45
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:47,640
Mercan?

46
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:49,240
Mercan, wake up!

47
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:00,160
No, no, no, no.

48
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:01,880
No. Don't you dare leave me.

49
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:05,440
Don't.

50
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:07,600
I won't let anything happen to you.

51
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:34,456
She has been sleeping since
she got back from the hospital.

52
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:36,560
Everything is normal
right now, don't worry.

53
00:03:37,040 --> 00:03:41,480
But due to Ms. Mercan's special
condition, she requires special care.

54
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:45,479
Organ transplant patients...

55
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:47,696
must live ten times more
carefully than other people.

56
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:50,640
You must never forget that her
immune system is highly sensitive.

57
00:03:50,920 --> 00:03:53,120
You will organize your
entire lives around this.

58
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:56,120
I will do whatever it takes.

59
00:03:57,240 --> 00:04:02,080
As you know, due to her condition, there
are lifelong medications she must take.

60
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:03,696
This is a matter of life and death.

61
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:06,160
Her diet also needs strict attention.

62
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:08,360
I know.

63
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:10,600
I will personally oversee
every single detail.

64
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:11,960
Make sure nothing is neglected.

65
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,160
If you'll excuse me.

66
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:15,800
Have a good day.

67
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:35,480
I've caused you so much pain.

68
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:39,320
I am the reason you are in this state.

69
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:48,320
You are everything to me, Mercan.

70
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,840
You are my whole life now.

71
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:01,600
There is nothing I wouldn't
do to make you smile.

72
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,600
Hah! Malik is here.

73
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:19,320
What happened?

74
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:23,360
Nothing. Without a passport,
nobody can do a thing.

75
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:28,600
We crossed the ocean
only to drown in a puddle.

76
00:05:29,320 --> 00:05:30,320
Don't even ask.

77
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:46,880
-Come, mother. -Aunt Binnaz.

78
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:49,560
Come sit, mom.

79
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:57,280
Ms. Mercan is doing quite well, thank
goodness. She regained consciousness.

80
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:02,000
Good, good.

81
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:03,600
Thank God.

82
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:06,160
What did you do? Did you find the passport?

83
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:08,800
-No. -It's nowhere to be found.

84
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:17,440
I hope it turns up too.
Health comes first, look.

85
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:19,760
Without it, there is no peace.

86
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:23,840
We'll look again, we'll turn the place
upside down and find it. Don't worry.

87
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:27,360
How many times have we looked everywhere,
mom? There's no place left to check.

88
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,440
If it were here, we would have found it.

89
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,920
It definitely slipped in somewhere.

90
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:36,800
It'll pop up in the most
unexpected place. You'll see.

91
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,520
I hope it happens just as you say.

92
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:56,960
Maybe if you had paid attention to this
instead of me, you might have found it.

93
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,720
Oh! My passport!

94
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,000
Ah!

95
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:15,640
Thank God!

96
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:19,120
Thank goodness! Where on
earth did you find it, Zehra?

97
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:23,160
Under the covers in the kitchen.

98
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,200
Of course!

99
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:36,320
I put it there the other day so it
wouldn't get wet while washing the car.

100
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:41,200
See?

101
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:47,440
Son, do you always carry
your passport on you?

102
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:50,000
I don't know. It was just a one-time thing.

103
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:51,920
Zehra...

104
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,920
Thank you so much, really, thank you.

105
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:03,080
God bless you, my dear.

106
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:06,440
Don't thank me at all. It means nothing.

107
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:12,240
You should have thought of
that before sinning against me...

108
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:23,280
I told you nobody treats an orphan well.

109
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:27,400
Here, you saw it for yourself...

110
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:30,280
How unfair you were,
accusing me right away.

111
00:08:34,040 --> 00:08:35,160
I am a woman all alone.

112
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:40,720
I thought getting married would save
me from loneliness, but I was wrong.

113
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:45,680
Don't say that, my Zehra. Look, God is
my witness. My mother and the rest too...

114
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:50,960
Look at the attitude she pulls
just because she got one thing right.

115
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:57,320
She isn't entirely wrong, though...

116
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:59,680
Yes, she has a point.

117
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:04,360
Are you happy now?

118
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:07,360
Very.

119
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:38,080
I can't get over this, Ateş.

120
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:40,600
It hurts so much.

121
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:45,440
I don't know how I can live with this pain.

122
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:55,800
Mercan?

123
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:58,520
Are you awake, my only one?

124
00:10:00,680 --> 00:10:01,800
Hold on.

125
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:03,920
Don't get up so suddenly.

126
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:06,520
You need to rest.

127
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:10,200
My whole body aches from lying down.

128
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:12,600
Let me get up a bit.

129
00:10:13,040 --> 00:10:14,040
No way.

130
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:18,520
I'm fine, there's nothing wrong with me.

131
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:22,640
It was just a minor fainting spell anyway.

132
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:24,400
You've completely exaggerated it.

133
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:27,840
Hospitals and all. I should get up now.

134
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:31,360
Be a good girl. We'll get along fine then.

135
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:35,280
You don't have to treat me well.

136
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:38,280
I know I don't.

137
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:43,760
This pain won't push us apart.

138
00:10:47,560 --> 00:10:49,640
Because nothing can ever push us apart.

139
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,720
Do you understand me?

140
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:58,840
Now, you will listen to me and stay in bed.

141
00:10:59,560 --> 00:11:00,960
Don't bother arguing.

142
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:03,360
You remember what the doctor said, right?

143
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,240
You need to rest.

144
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:08,560
I will argue.

145
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:11,440
Because I am fine. I want to get up.

146
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:14,360
You can't even go an hour
without arguing, can you?

147
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:16,600
Not true at all.

148
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:19,800
You make it sound like I oppose everything!

149
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:23,320
Of course, dear, you're so right.

150
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:25,800
Have a heart, really.

151
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:28,920
I'd rather have yours.

152
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:33,400
Look at what she's still saying...

153
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,520
Shall we make a bet?

154
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:41,240
Don't get upset when you lose now.

155
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:43,000
Let me get your medicine.

156
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:47,200
Whoa!

157
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:52,080
See, you don't listen. And you
want to make a bet on top of it.

158
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:56,880
I'll tell you what.

159
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:03,040
You won't argue with me for
a whole day. That's the bet.

160
00:12:05,040 --> 00:12:06,080
Are you in?

161
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:08,520
Alright. For what?

162
00:12:09,560 --> 00:12:11,760
You name it. I accept anything in advance.

163
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,200
Okay.

164
00:12:16,680 --> 00:12:18,840
For a whole day, you
will do whatever I want.

165
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:23,040
We'll spend time together, go out...

166
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:24,960
Whatever I want...

167
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:29,120
Deal. And if I win...

168
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:35,600
I'll tell you when I win.

169
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:38,520
No, you have to tell me. I'll get curious.

170
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:41,440
Since you're going to
win, why are you so curious?

171
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:45,760
Unless you're certain
you'll lose, of course?

172
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:48,000
I will never lose.

173
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:54,656
Now, you are going back to
bed and you are not getting up.

174
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:55,920
I'll go get your pills.

175
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:02,040
Good girl. Always be this well-behaved.

176
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:13,440
I can't lose you too, Mercan!

177
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:31,680
I brought some tea.

178
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,640
Good job, dear, thank you.

179
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:37,760
Thank God we got through this one too.

180
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:40,560
I guess there isn't another
crisis waiting at the door, right?

181
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:43,760
I hope so, but...

182
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:46,040
We did Zehra wrong, too.

183
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:50,760
I mean...

184
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:54,360
Even though I don't like
her... Yes, we were a bit unfair.

185
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:58,440
If it weren't for her, Malik would be gone.

186
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:00,960
The girl literally came to our rescue.

187
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:05,560
Besides, accusing an
innocent person offends God.

188
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:10,840
We need to make it up to Zehra.

189
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:13,720
We should, but...

190
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:15,720
I'm telling you, her
sulking will never end.

191
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:20,480
She'll parade around for two
years saying how right she was.

192
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,560
Well... Let that be the
price for the sin we committed.

193
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:25,880
We need to win her over.

194
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:29,200
So, what will we do?
How do we make it right?

195
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:36,160
Welcome.

196
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,640
We were just worried about Mercan.

197
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:55,400
We thought we'd drop by.

198
00:14:56,400 --> 00:14:57,400
How is she now?

199
00:14:58,600 --> 00:14:59,600
Better.

200
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:01,240
Who knows what you did to her?

201
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,200
Mercan is sick, don't you hear?

202
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:10,800
Ateş, I want to see her.

203
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:13,920
Seeing you will be good for her too.

204
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:25,320
Look...

205
00:15:26,880 --> 00:15:28,160
I don't want a scene.

206
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:32,800
The doctor said she needs
to stay away from stress.

207
00:15:33,920 --> 00:15:34,920
How wonderful.

208
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:39,200
Then all of you Karahans, pack
your bags and get the hell out.

209
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:41,240
There's no greater stress than you.

210
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:43,640
Look, Nezir!

211
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:47,520
I love disappointing you.

212
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:51,760
This is my house.

213
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:54,560
I have no intention of going anywhere.

214
00:15:57,040 --> 00:15:59,120
You are the reason for
what Mercan is going through!

215
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:02,240
If you truly loved Mercan,
you would stay away from her.

216
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:05,160
You'd protect her from
your family's wickedness too.

217
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:09,360
And you're the one who's
going to protect her?

218
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:13,520
You can hit me...

219
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:16,240
You can beat me...

220
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:17,680
You can kick me out...

221
00:16:18,640 --> 00:16:20,440
You know I'm right, too.

222
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:23,600
If Mercan is in this
state, it's because of you.

223
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,000
Nezir!

224
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:28,400
Get out!

225
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:49,200
Are you comfortable?

226
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:54,400
I'm comfortable, I'm fine...

227
00:16:55,680 --> 00:16:57,120
Stop exaggerating this.

228
00:16:57,880 --> 00:16:58,920
Both you and Ateş...

229
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:02,240
You are not fine.

230
00:17:03,280 --> 00:17:04,560
I know you. What happened?

231
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:09,920
There isn't an issue with Ateş, is there?

232
00:17:16,880 --> 00:17:18,800
Turns out, everything was my fault.

233
00:17:23,040 --> 00:17:25,040
I caused Eylül's death.

234
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:31,240
Wait a minute... What does that mean?!

235
00:17:32,840 --> 00:17:33,840
I...

236
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:38,920
I am living with Eylül's kidney, Demet.

237
00:17:46,760 --> 00:17:49,280
They transplanted her kidney into me.

238
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:54,960
And she...

239
00:17:56,720 --> 00:17:58,440
Eylül couldn't handle the surgery and...

240
00:18:00,520 --> 00:18:01,520
She died.

241
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:06,400
Ateş just found this out too.

242
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:14,400
I am so sorry, Mercan.

243
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:19,240
Me too.

244
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:21,080
Me too.

245
00:18:24,760 --> 00:18:26,480
You have no fault in this, Mercan...

246
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:28,440
None at all.

247
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:31,880
It doesn't change the outcome.

248
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:35,200
My life cost her hers...

249
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:41,560
How did Ateş react to it?

250
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:48,760
He's trying to stand
strong so I don't get upset.

251
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:52,560
It's so hard.

252
00:18:54,280 --> 00:18:55,480
Like a nightmare...

253
00:18:57,520 --> 00:18:59,280
Normally, I should leave, right?

254
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:03,960
Because the longer I stay here...

255
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:08,880
I remind the man I love of
his greatest pain in life.

256
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:13,600
But I can't leave either.

257
00:19:16,520 --> 00:19:18,760
My love is just that immense, Demet.

258
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:24,240
That's why my struggle is so immense too.

259
00:19:26,560 --> 00:19:28,160
One part of me says go.

260
00:19:28,880 --> 00:19:30,080
The other part says stay.

261
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:36,680
I don't know what to do...

262
00:19:43,680 --> 00:19:44,680
My dear.

263
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:02,440
I should get going, see you later.

264
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:04,200
See you.

265
00:21:18,160 --> 00:21:19,560
Could you watch where you're going?

266
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:24,120
What are you doing, why
are you holding me like that?

267
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:26,240
What are you talking about?
You think I'm so eager?

268
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:27,800
I caught you so you wouldn't fall.

269
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:30,720
As if I'm dying to hold you.

270
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:32,640
God, give me patience.

271
00:21:33,520 --> 00:21:34,680
Watch your step too.

272
00:21:35,480 --> 00:21:37,761
Okay, Demet, okay. I promise
I won't catch you next time.

273
00:21:38,880 --> 00:21:41,480
You'll find yourself on the
floor. And don't complain to me then.

274
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:49,480
- What the hell is going on here?
- Brother, it's nothing. We're just talking.

275
00:21:50,040 --> 00:21:51,760
What do you mean "hell"? You got a problem?

276
00:21:52,360 --> 00:21:53,800
Watch your mouth.

277
00:21:54,440 --> 00:21:56,456
I'll leave a little signature on you.
You won't recognize yourself in the mirror.

278
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:57,840
Look at you! Back off, man!

279
00:21:58,280 --> 00:22:01,320
What are you guys doing? Come on, walk.

280
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:06,800
You taught me to be patient.

281
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:08,640
You just keep on being patient.

282
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:11,936
We'll cross paths eventually.

283
00:22:11,960 --> 00:22:13,000
Inevitably.
I will see you.

284
00:22:26,680 --> 00:22:27,680
Ah!

285
00:22:27,840 --> 00:22:29,040
A sudden chill came over me.

286
00:22:30,280 --> 00:22:31,280
Zehra!

287
00:22:32,040 --> 00:22:33,040
Zehra!

288
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,680
It's as if we pay them a salary
just so they can disappear!

289
00:22:38,120 --> 00:22:40,080
When you need them, they
are nowhere to be found.

290
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:44,720
I'm going to put something on.

291
00:23:00,720 --> 00:23:02,320
Unregistered number.

292
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:04,240
Hello?

293
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:07,480
What happened, mom? Who was that?

294
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:10,000
Nobody important, dear.

295
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:12,600
A friend from the
foundation was going to call.

296
00:23:12,880 --> 00:23:14,280
I'm not in the mood to talk at all.

297
00:23:15,040 --> 00:23:17,120
I hung up so she
wouldn't bother you either.

298
00:23:17,360 --> 00:23:18,520
She talks way too much.

299
00:23:21,240 --> 00:23:23,000
Let me grab something
to wear and come back.

300
00:23:25,840 --> 00:23:30,000
You're up to something, but
it'll come out eventually...

301
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:45,760
My wife.

302
00:23:46,520 --> 00:23:47,960
My one and only wife.

303
00:23:48,840 --> 00:23:49,920
My sweet wife.

304
00:23:50,480 --> 00:23:51,480
What's up?

305
00:23:54,760 --> 00:23:56,680
Wifey, I...

306
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:59,440
I deeply apologize on behalf of my family.

307
00:24:02,280 --> 00:24:03,360
"On behalf of your family"?

308
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:04,280
Hm-hmm.

309
00:24:04,360 --> 00:24:06,840
Interesting, how did
you slip out of the blame?

310
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:10,200
-Me? -Hmm?

311
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:13,559
It wasn't just them, you
falsely accused me too.

312
00:24:13,560 --> 00:24:14,840
You suspected me too.

313
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:22,280
You're right, but I swear I
didn't blame you as much as they did.

314
00:24:23,160 --> 00:24:24,160
I swear.

315
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:29,720
God is my witness, I didn't
let them say a word against you.

316
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:31,456
They couldn't say a single thing.

317
00:24:31,480 --> 00:24:33,800
Hmm... Sure, I bet that's
exactly what happened.

318
00:24:45,920 --> 00:24:47,480
I apologize on my own behalf as well.

319
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:57,920
Come on, forgive me, rose of roses...

320
00:24:58,640 --> 00:24:59,640
Of my garden...

321
00:25:03,040 --> 00:25:04,040
Rose of my heart!

322
00:25:05,800 --> 00:25:07,240
The most beautiful rose in my world!

323
00:25:21,720 --> 00:25:25,760
I am not going to forget what happened
just because you shove a rose in my face.

324
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:30,960
You all already treat me
like a thorn, not a rose.

325
00:25:32,440 --> 00:25:34,496
Instead of chasing after
me with flowers and bugs...

326
00:25:34,520 --> 00:25:37,480
learn to stand behind your wife.

327
00:25:38,680 --> 00:25:39,680
You're right.

328
00:25:39,960 --> 00:25:41,600
Enough, you're right!

329
00:25:41,640 --> 00:25:43,520
- All you say is "You're right."
- You're right!

330
00:25:44,560 --> 00:25:45,880
I swear.

331
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:47,920
Our folks...

332
00:25:48,960 --> 00:25:50,320
I think they learned their lesson.

333
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:51,840
Especially me!

334
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:54,800
I learned my lesson the hard
way. Nobody could hold me back.

335
00:25:55,360 --> 00:25:57,600
They cried, "Berat! Berat!"
But I learned my lesson.

336
00:25:57,640 --> 00:25:59,560
Hmm, sure, that's exactly how it went.

337
00:26:00,080 --> 00:26:01,200
Forgive us, wifey.

338
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:02,960
Forgive us.

339
00:26:06,360 --> 00:26:07,360
Forgive us, wifey.

340
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:15,720
I don't trust you anymore.

341
00:26:16,840 --> 00:26:18,760
What difference does it
make if I forgive you...

342
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:24,240
The branch forgives the
wind, but it's already broken.

343
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:40,400
Oh, Zehra.

344
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:43,960
Oh, my rose, oh, my wife.

345
00:26:46,080 --> 00:26:47,200
What is Berat to do?

346
00:28:19,800 --> 00:28:21,040
Could it be one of these...

347
00:28:22,120 --> 00:28:23,200
Let me try.

348
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:40,600
It's cold here, you'll catch
a chill. Let's go inside.

349
00:28:44,760 --> 00:28:46,160
Yes, we can go in, of course.

350
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:48,520
I'm just sitting out here for you anyway.

351
00:28:49,520 --> 00:28:50,520
I mean...

352
00:28:51,760 --> 00:28:56,240
If you want, we can stay... We
can go... It doesn't matter to me.

353
00:28:58,400 --> 00:29:00,560
Alright, I really want
to, yes, you're right.

354
00:29:01,840 --> 00:29:02,920
Let's stay a little longer.

355
00:29:04,760 --> 00:29:06,280
Let me get a shawl for your shoulders.

356
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:20,480
If you make this a habit, I'll
always want this much attention.

357
00:29:23,040 --> 00:29:24,640
As long as you are well.

358
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:29,400
I will shower you with
attention for the rest of my life.

359
00:29:33,400 --> 00:29:35,040
Are you really determined not to tell me?

360
00:29:36,080 --> 00:29:37,720
What you'll ask for if you win, I mean?

361
00:29:38,560 --> 00:29:40,920
Yes. Let it be a mystery to you.

362
00:29:42,840 --> 00:29:44,720
Since you're going to
lose, there's no problem.

363
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:46,720
You'll just tell me then.

364
00:29:47,520 --> 00:29:49,160
Either way, I'm the winner.

365
00:29:50,040 --> 00:29:52,600
Even if it's just for one day,
look, you stopped being stubborn.

366
00:29:54,040 --> 00:29:55,800
I can deal with all sorts of hardships.

367
00:29:56,760 --> 00:29:59,480
But I can't deal with your stubbornness.

368
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:02,680
It has the strength of a hundred tigers...

369
00:30:03,040 --> 00:30:05,960
Well... Every beautiful
thing comes with a hardship.

370
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:10,840
You can't always be the
one doing the burning.

371
00:30:11,720 --> 00:30:13,680
Sometimes, you will be
the one to burn, Mr. Ateş.

372
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:16,680
I'll burn.

373
00:30:20,040 --> 00:30:21,680
If it's for you, I'll gladly burn, but...

374
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:25,480
Ateş.

375
00:30:26,640 --> 00:30:28,600
Tell me, my heart.

376
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:32,080
Sometimes...

377
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:35,200
I feel like I will never be able to heal.

378
00:30:37,200 --> 00:30:40,000
Like I will never be happy again.

379
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:44,440
Then you look at me with a smile.

380
00:30:45,400 --> 00:30:46,400
Everything changes.

381
00:30:51,880 --> 00:30:53,360
You are not a choice for me...

382
00:30:55,640 --> 00:30:57,720
You are my destiny that I
cannot give up on, Mercan.

383
00:31:00,480 --> 00:31:02,080
There is an unbreakable bond between us.

384
00:31:05,040 --> 00:31:07,440
It is a bond sealed by
the beating of our hearts.

385
00:31:11,200 --> 00:31:12,320
There is nothing to be done.

386
00:31:13,760 --> 00:31:14,760
And nowhere to run...

387
00:31:16,720 --> 00:31:18,680
No matter how far apart we are...

388
00:31:19,960 --> 00:31:21,280
those bonds will always be there.

389
00:31:24,920 --> 00:31:27,120
We are two halves that complete each other.

390
00:31:28,760 --> 00:31:30,800
And you know, one cannot live incomplete.

391
00:31:42,280 --> 00:31:44,400
The safest place in
the world is right here.

392
00:31:47,040 --> 00:31:48,680
The beating of your heart gives me peace.

393
00:31:51,360 --> 00:31:52,760
Next to you, I feel...

394
00:31:54,400 --> 00:31:56,080
strong and protected.

395
00:31:59,080 --> 00:32:00,080
You are my...

396
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:02,920
most beautiful sanctuary.

397
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:05,800
My most peaceful harbor.

398
00:32:16,800 --> 00:32:19,120
Come on, let's go inside. Don't freeze.

399
00:32:20,520 --> 00:32:21,760
I should go check on Cemal too.

400
00:32:22,080 --> 00:32:23,080
I'm not cold.

401
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:28,320
But let's go inside, of course.

402
00:32:29,400 --> 00:32:31,840
Otherwise, you'll fall behind on your work.

403
00:32:33,520 --> 00:32:35,280
You got excited for nothing, Ateş Karahan.

404
00:32:36,320 --> 00:32:37,360
You are not going to win.

405
00:33:03,240 --> 00:33:04,240
Haydar!

406
00:33:08,720 --> 00:33:09,720
Nermin!

407
00:33:10,680 --> 00:33:12,680
I found keys in Ateş's study.

408
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:14,200
I'm going to try them now.

409
00:33:16,400 --> 00:33:17,400
Hurry up!

410
00:33:19,840 --> 00:33:21,080
No, not this one either.

411
00:33:25,800 --> 00:33:27,800
No, this didn't work either.

412
00:33:30,680 --> 00:33:31,680
Not this one either.

413
00:33:35,160 --> 00:33:37,200
It worked! Oh, it worked!

414
00:33:41,280 --> 00:33:42,280
Thank God!

415
00:33:43,080 --> 00:33:44,720
Ugh... What is this place!?

416
00:33:45,920 --> 00:33:48,160
This clearly isn't a five-star hotel!

417
00:33:49,240 --> 00:33:50,760
Be grateful I didn't die in this dump!

418
00:33:52,240 --> 00:33:53,240
Move, come on, move...

419
00:34:06,840 --> 00:34:07,840
What's going on...

420
00:34:08,240 --> 00:34:10,000
Husband and wife out for a stroll?

421
00:34:18,040 --> 00:34:19,400
And without asking for permission?

422
00:34:31,080 --> 00:34:32,880
Did you think I was stupid!

423
00:34:34,200 --> 00:34:35,880
Do you think I'd let you escape!

424
00:34:48,560 --> 00:34:49,800
Do you think you're clever!

425
00:34:54,800 --> 00:34:55,800
-Move. -Let go!

426
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:57,560
-I said move! -I said let go!

427
00:34:59,240 --> 00:35:00,280
-Scumbags! -Get inside!

428
00:35:00,920 --> 00:35:02,160
Let go!

429
00:35:20,320 --> 00:35:21,760
This is your game, isn't it?

430
00:35:24,920 --> 00:35:26,360
You did this on purpose, didn't you!

431
00:35:27,120 --> 00:35:29,080
You left the keys on purpose!?

432
00:35:30,080 --> 00:35:31,320
Now you get it!

433
00:35:32,040 --> 00:35:34,680
I will play with you like
a cat plays with a mouse.

434
00:35:39,040 --> 00:35:40,040
Get me out of here!

435
00:35:41,080 --> 00:35:42,080
Nermin!

436
00:35:45,520 --> 00:35:46,520
Walk.

437
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:51,480
Get me out of here!

438
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:53,000
Nermin!

439
00:36:00,880 --> 00:36:03,760
Don't try to ease your conscience
by blaming it all on your father.

440
00:36:04,680 --> 00:36:06,080
You are Eylül's killer.

441
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:08,200
Ateş knows this too.

442
00:36:09,240 --> 00:36:10,240
Stay away from him!

443
00:36:16,520 --> 00:36:18,440
There's a wound in Ateş's
heart for his sister.

444
00:36:19,080 --> 00:36:21,160
Every time he sees you, that wound bleeds.

445
00:36:28,640 --> 00:36:30,600
Do you think anyone would
want to live like this?

446
00:36:31,720 --> 00:36:32,720
Of course not!

447
00:36:34,280 --> 00:36:36,760
Leave me alone. Get out of my way.

448
00:36:41,040 --> 00:36:42,720
Then get out of Ateş's way.

449
00:36:44,120 --> 00:36:45,240
You will leave him alone!

450
00:36:46,360 --> 00:36:47,360
What's it to you!

451
00:36:49,840 --> 00:36:52,560
You don't even care about the
state you've dragged him into, do you?

452
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:54,560
Supposedly, you love him!

453
00:36:55,840 --> 00:36:58,200
If you loved him, you
would stay away from him.

454
00:37:01,600 --> 00:37:05,200
What you do is nothing but stabbing
him with a knife every single day!

455
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:14,960
Love is not like this!

456
00:37:15,680 --> 00:37:17,320
What do you know about love!

457
00:37:18,080 --> 00:37:19,080
Look at me!

458
00:37:22,120 --> 00:37:23,920
-I swear I'll... -Aslı!

459
00:37:46,200 --> 00:37:47,200
My God.

460
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:50,120
What a heavy burden this is.

461
00:37:51,360 --> 00:37:53,640
How am I going to carry
this for the rest of my life?

462
00:38:25,160 --> 00:38:27,560
I told Mother Müzeyyen so many
times, but she didn't listen.

463
00:38:27,960 --> 00:38:28,960
She will listen to you.

464
00:38:33,040 --> 00:38:34,520
We need to talk to her.

465
00:38:38,240 --> 00:38:39,920
Fine, Haydar is a bad man and all, but...

466
00:38:40,600 --> 00:38:43,280
I don't know, doing this doesn't suit us.

467
00:38:52,680 --> 00:38:53,960
Mother Müzeyyen's goal...

468
00:38:55,400 --> 00:38:56,520
is not to get revenge.

469
00:38:58,920 --> 00:38:59,920
It's to torture.

470
00:39:08,560 --> 00:39:10,120
We need to keep her under control.

471
00:39:16,840 --> 00:39:19,640
She doesn't separate the
guilty from the innocent.

472
00:39:21,840 --> 00:39:22,840
We will separate them.

473
00:39:29,080 --> 00:39:30,360
The issue isn't Haydar anyway...

474
00:39:31,640 --> 00:39:32,640
The issue is Mercan.

475
00:39:38,760 --> 00:39:39,960
How is she? Is she okay?

476
00:39:41,520 --> 00:39:42,520
Better.

477
00:39:43,760 --> 00:39:44,800
She's trying to recover...

478
00:39:50,960 --> 00:39:53,200
You know Mercan made me a
completely different person.

479
00:39:59,760 --> 00:40:02,720
I thought there was nothing
but pain and revenge inside me.

480
00:40:11,080 --> 00:40:13,240
Turns out there were other
things I didn't know about.

481
00:40:14,280 --> 00:40:15,280
Beautiful things...

482
00:40:17,880 --> 00:40:19,840
Beautiful things... Like love, huh?

483
00:40:22,080 --> 00:40:23,760
There is nothing I wouldn't do for her.

484
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:26,440
I'd lay down my life for
her without blinking an eye.

485
00:40:27,120 --> 00:40:28,480
But the matter isn't my life.

486
00:40:36,480 --> 00:40:37,960
Every time Eylül comes to my mind...

487
00:40:38,920 --> 00:40:40,400
Not that she ever leaves it anyway...

488
00:40:43,200 --> 00:40:45,200
that war inside me starts all over again.

489
00:40:56,160 --> 00:40:57,960
As great as my feelings for Mercan are...

490
00:40:59,640 --> 00:41:01,400
the pain of losing Eylül is just as great.

491
00:41:06,120 --> 00:41:07,800
I wish I wasn't trapped in such a dilemma.

492
00:41:14,600 --> 00:41:15,680
Being stuck in purgatory...

493
00:41:18,160 --> 00:41:19,880
is worse than burning in hell.

494
00:41:36,400 --> 00:41:37,880
She is suffering because of me.

495
00:41:50,680 --> 00:41:52,520
But rather than living without Mercan,

496
00:41:55,040 --> 00:41:56,040
I am willing to burn.

497
00:42:04,800 --> 00:42:06,560
There is no life for
me without her anymore.

498
00:42:25,400 --> 00:42:29,960
(singing)

499
00:42:31,520 --> 00:42:32,520
Hello!

500
00:42:33,280 --> 00:42:34,520
Thank you!

501
00:42:35,280 --> 00:42:37,960
I gave the documents to
Mr. Cemal. We got it done.

502
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:40,720
Nothing will tear us apart anymore.

503
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:43,160
I've already started
preparing for the celebration.

504
00:42:43,400 --> 00:42:46,400
I'm making your favorite
carrot walnut cake!

505
00:42:48,600 --> 00:42:49,640
It looks so good!

506
00:42:51,840 --> 00:42:54,560
You'll keep making such nice things
after we get married too, right?

507
00:42:54,720 --> 00:42:56,680
If you are a good husband, why not.

508
00:42:57,320 --> 00:42:58,520
Of course I will be!

509
00:42:59,520 --> 00:43:00,920
I want Çiçek's cake!

510
00:43:01,440 --> 00:43:04,600
- Because that's the best one.
- Malik! Be quiet!

511
00:43:06,280 --> 00:43:08,480
My system can't handle this much romance.

512
00:43:08,920 --> 00:43:10,880
You'll just have to make
do with carrot for now!

513
00:43:11,520 --> 00:43:12,520
Çiçek...

514
00:43:13,720 --> 00:43:15,560
As long as it's made by your hands...

515
00:43:16,680 --> 00:43:17,680
It doesn't matter.

516
00:43:19,200 --> 00:43:20,200
Look!

517
00:43:21,160 --> 00:43:22,520
It looks so beautiful!

518
00:43:26,040 --> 00:43:27,160
It's turned out wonderfully!

519
00:43:27,280 --> 00:43:29,840
It's as if the beauty of
your face has rubbed off on it.

520
00:43:32,720 --> 00:43:33,816
So you're skilled around the house?

521
00:43:33,840 --> 00:43:36,240
Well... We aren't useless, you know.

522
00:43:57,560 --> 00:44:00,560
