529
00:44:17,880 --> 00:44:18,880
Open settings.

530
00:44:18,881 --> 00:44:21,399
Choose Audio Track and pick your language.

531
00:44:21,400 --> 00:44:24,680
The full Audio track upload
schedule is in the description below.

532
00:44:46,480 --> 00:44:48,280
As great as my feelings for Mercan are...

533
00:44:49,920 --> 00:44:51,680
the pain of losing Eylül is just as great.

534
00:44:53,200 --> 00:44:54,880
I wish I wasn't trapped in such a dilemma.

535
00:45:14,360 --> 00:45:15,440
Being stuck in purgatory...

536
00:45:17,880 --> 00:45:19,680
is worse than burning in hell.

537
00:45:44,160 --> 00:45:45,240
Why aren't you in the room?

538
00:45:47,760 --> 00:45:48,760
Umm...

539
00:45:50,280 --> 00:45:52,000
I just came out to get some fresh air.

540
00:45:52,880 --> 00:45:54,920
Look at the weather,
there's a storm. Come on...

541
00:45:59,720 --> 00:46:01,880
I'm not protesting.

542
00:46:02,880 --> 00:46:04,616
I pulled my arm away
because I can walk myself.

543
00:46:04,640 --> 00:46:06,120
So I wouldn't burden you.

544
00:46:07,160 --> 00:46:08,600
But there's no fun in it like this.

545
00:46:09,640 --> 00:46:12,400
Why not? I said okay, I'm coming.

546
00:46:17,040 --> 00:46:18,040
What are you doing!?

547
00:46:18,720 --> 00:46:20,000
I was prepared for this.

548
00:46:21,400 --> 00:46:23,720
You were going to protest,
and I was going to carry you.

549
00:46:25,280 --> 00:46:26,760
I told you I wouldn't lose.

550
00:46:27,640 --> 00:46:28,760
Yes! You did tell me.

551
00:46:33,360 --> 00:46:34,400
Well... but wait a minute!

552
00:46:37,320 --> 00:46:38,320
What happened now?

553
00:46:39,200 --> 00:46:41,040
Well... I got hungry.

554
00:46:43,120 --> 00:46:44,120
Okay.

555
00:46:44,720 --> 00:46:47,560
Okay, let me take you to the room,
I'll prepare something and bring it.

556
00:46:48,400 --> 00:46:50,760
Alright. I can help you if you want.

557
00:46:51,120 --> 00:46:55,240
If you want, sure. Otherwise, I
can go to my room, it's not a problem.

558
00:46:56,240 --> 00:46:57,680
You are very persistent, very.

559
00:46:59,240 --> 00:47:00,240
I am indeed.

560
00:47:19,320 --> 00:47:20,320
Well, put me down then.

561
00:47:22,160 --> 00:47:23,520
I said I would walk, though.

562
00:47:43,640 --> 00:47:45,280
What should we make, what would you like?

563
00:47:47,320 --> 00:47:51,520
A toast would be good. Like
one with feta cheese and thyme...

564
00:47:52,360 --> 00:47:54,640
Ugh, I'm getting hungrier
just talking about it.

565
00:47:55,320 --> 00:47:57,120
Okay, you sit down, I'll handle it.

566
00:48:12,800 --> 00:48:15,440
Don't look at me like that,
I didn't protest or anything.

567
00:48:16,120 --> 00:48:17,640
I got up and I'm standing next to you.

568
00:48:19,080 --> 00:48:20,160
Okay, I didn't say a thing.

569
00:48:49,400 --> 00:48:50,400
Wait a minute...

570
00:48:51,440 --> 00:48:53,000
A very important ingredient is missing.

571
00:48:57,560 --> 00:48:58,560
You couldn't find it.

572
00:48:59,640 --> 00:49:02,080
Whereas Tahir would spread it
on bread and bring it to me...

573
00:49:06,320 --> 00:49:07,320
Tomato paste.

574
00:50:19,160 --> 00:50:21,760
Let's complete everything
left unfinished, together.

575
00:50:27,880 --> 00:50:28,920
Should I make tea for you?

576
00:50:29,880 --> 00:50:30,880
Please do.

577
00:50:31,480 --> 00:50:33,040
Steeped dark, just the way you like it.

578
00:50:34,680 --> 00:50:36,120
You're the only one I like.

579
00:50:47,800 --> 00:50:49,960
This toast is going to be
incredibly good, by the way.

580
00:50:50,880 --> 00:50:51,880
Why is that?

581
00:50:52,560 --> 00:50:53,640
You touched it.

582
00:50:55,520 --> 00:50:58,360
I want you to make the exact
same toast with the same touch.

583
00:50:59,400 --> 00:51:00,400
Alright.

584
00:51:03,480 --> 00:51:04,880
Well, weren't you making tea?

585
00:51:07,600 --> 00:51:09,600
But you made me forget.

586
00:51:11,080 --> 00:51:12,240
Did I steal your mind?

587
00:51:14,320 --> 00:51:15,320
A little bit.

588
00:51:17,440 --> 00:51:18,440
And you have mine.

589
00:51:20,160 --> 00:51:21,160
So we're even.

590
00:52:26,040 --> 00:52:27,040
What happened, son?

591
00:52:46,120 --> 00:52:47,400
It's because of Zehra, isn't it?

592
00:52:50,760 --> 00:52:52,120
I told you.

593
00:52:52,360 --> 00:52:54,160
I told you that girl was no good, didn't I?

594
00:52:56,720 --> 00:52:59,360
But what did you do? You
went and acted stubbornly.

595
00:53:00,880 --> 00:53:05,760
He who doesn't listen to his mother ends up sitting
and listening to his own misery, just like this.

596
00:53:09,360 --> 00:53:10,760
Why are you talking like this, mom?

597
00:53:14,920 --> 00:53:16,160
I love Zehra.

598
00:53:19,040 --> 00:53:20,480
My heart beats for her.

599
00:53:22,160 --> 00:53:23,880
Should I tell it to stop? What should I do?

600
00:53:25,440 --> 00:53:28,880
Turns out I had a heart too.
Turns out it actually worked.

601
00:53:34,440 --> 00:53:35,680
She loves me too.

602
00:53:37,120 --> 00:53:38,280
In her own way, I guess.

603
00:53:40,440 --> 00:53:42,640
I wanted to build a family with her.

604
00:53:43,760 --> 00:53:45,560
Did I ask for too much?

605
00:53:47,320 --> 00:53:51,040
If you think I'm going to divorce
her, stop thinking that, mother. I won't.

606
00:53:54,680 --> 00:53:57,760
I won't do what my father
did to us. I won't do it.

607
00:53:58,560 --> 00:53:59,560
Do you understand?

608
00:53:59,720 --> 00:54:01,120
I won't abandon someone halfway.

609
00:54:03,360 --> 00:54:06,200
I accept her. The good and the bad.

610
00:54:08,440 --> 00:54:09,440
She is my wife.

611
00:54:11,640 --> 00:54:13,976
I want to be a family with her. I want
to be happy. Am I asking for too much?

612
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:15,000
Am I asking for too much?

613
00:54:19,320 --> 00:54:20,640
How could it be too much, my son?

614
00:54:21,640 --> 00:54:22,640
Is that even possible?

615
00:54:23,760 --> 00:54:25,800
You deserve the absolute
best of everything.

616
00:54:29,040 --> 00:54:32,800
Zehra should get down on her knees and pray
in gratitude for finding someone like you.

617
00:54:35,320 --> 00:54:40,800
I only said that so you wouldn't open your heart
to someone who doesn't know its worth, but...

618
00:54:46,960 --> 00:54:48,440
With a heart like yours...

619
00:54:50,720 --> 00:54:53,120
Zehra will surely see and
understand its worth eventually...

620
00:54:58,440 --> 00:54:59,960
Come here, come!

621
00:55:53,040 --> 00:55:55,000
Shh! Stop, leave it to me.

622
00:56:15,520 --> 00:56:17,640
If you're going to constantly
fuss over me like this,

623
00:56:18,040 --> 00:56:19,560
I'll never get well, I'm telling you.

624
00:56:25,120 --> 00:56:26,920
Let's make a deal right now, then.

625
00:56:28,440 --> 00:56:29,760
You get well.

626
00:56:30,760 --> 00:56:32,120
And I keep doing all these things.

627
00:56:33,040 --> 00:56:34,040
How about it?

628
00:56:34,920 --> 00:56:37,120
-Deal. -Deal.

629
00:56:38,760 --> 00:56:39,760
I'm surprised.

630
00:56:40,960 --> 00:56:41,960
You didn't argue again.

631
00:56:43,240 --> 00:56:45,560
I'm starting to feel like
you're going to win the bet too.

632
00:56:47,440 --> 00:56:48,440
I told you.

633
00:56:49,240 --> 00:56:50,440
I don't like losing.

634
00:56:53,080 --> 00:56:54,080
Come on, go to sleep.

635
00:57:07,440 --> 00:57:08,440
Stay with me.

636
00:57:10,160 --> 00:57:11,280
I'm right here, don't worry.

637
00:57:20,960 --> 00:57:24,600
Tell me a fairy tale with a happy ending.

638
00:57:26,560 --> 00:57:27,560
A fairy tale?

639
00:57:28,960 --> 00:57:30,120
I don't know any fairy tales.

640
00:57:32,000 --> 00:57:33,240
Write one for us.

641
00:57:34,760 --> 00:57:36,040
But I'm a terrible storyteller.

642
00:57:37,600 --> 00:57:38,680
I would never believe that.

643
00:57:41,600 --> 00:57:42,720
Don't say I didn't warn you.

644
00:57:46,160 --> 00:57:47,160
Are you ready?

645
00:57:47,760 --> 00:57:48,840
Very ready.

646
00:57:50,320 --> 00:57:51,320
In that case...

647
00:57:53,560 --> 00:57:56,880
Once upon a time, there was a
sweet, little house by the beach.

648
00:57:57,960 --> 00:57:59,080
Two rooms and a living room.

649
00:58:00,480 --> 00:58:02,280
In it lived a beautiful, beautiful woman...

650
00:58:03,120 --> 00:58:05,240
and a man who loved her very much.

651
00:58:07,760 --> 00:58:09,960
And the man was quite handsome.

652
00:58:12,160 --> 00:58:15,440
If he looked like you, he must
have been incredibly handsome.

653
00:58:16,880 --> 00:58:18,200
Just like me.

654
00:58:19,280 --> 00:58:21,400
Let's not interfere with
our fairy tale, though.

655
00:58:22,880 --> 00:58:23,880
Okay.

656
00:58:26,000 --> 00:58:29,280
The husband and wife supported each
other, always living hand in hand...

657
00:58:31,360 --> 00:58:32,800
They had two children as well.

658
00:58:34,280 --> 00:58:35,280
Yes.

659
00:58:36,080 --> 00:58:38,800
They had two children. A boy and a girl.

660
00:58:39,880 --> 00:58:43,200
The boy was handsome like his father...

661
00:58:44,280 --> 00:58:45,280
And the girl was...

662
00:58:46,840 --> 00:58:48,480
a water nymph, just like her mother.

663
00:58:50,360 --> 00:58:51,360
However...

664
00:58:52,200 --> 00:58:54,560
The man wanted more children.

665
00:58:55,480 --> 00:58:56,920
He always said two wasn't enough.

666
00:58:58,960 --> 00:59:00,400
Maybe you shouldn't exaggerate?

667
00:59:02,000 --> 00:59:04,160
Let's always exaggerate the kid part.

668
00:59:07,120 --> 00:59:08,400
If we go back to our fairy tale?

669
00:59:13,720 --> 00:59:16,360
Every day, as the man brought
home the delicious fish he caught,

670
00:59:17,040 --> 00:59:18,400
he'd pull a pearl from the sea.

671
00:59:20,120 --> 00:59:22,800
Then he made a necklace out
of those pearls for his wife.

672
00:59:25,440 --> 00:59:26,960
He gave the necklace to his wife.

673
00:59:27,920 --> 00:59:30,800
Since the woman was overjoyed by
everything that came from her husband,

674
00:59:31,240 --> 00:59:32,520
she was overjoyed by this too...

675
00:59:33,760 --> 00:59:35,000
That's exactly how it happened.

676
00:59:36,120 --> 00:59:37,680
The woman loved the necklace very much.

677
00:59:38,560 --> 00:59:40,280
But then one day, she lost it...

678
00:59:41,400 --> 00:59:42,680
The man looked everywhere.

679
00:59:43,520 --> 00:59:44,760
But he couldn't find it.

680
00:59:47,120 --> 00:59:50,480
The woman was heartbroken
because she lost her husband's gift.

681
00:59:53,560 --> 00:59:56,800
The man told her, "You
are my greatest pearl."

682
00:59:58,520 --> 00:59:59,680
He comforted his wife.

683
01:00:03,840 --> 01:00:06,680
They both thought about
how lucky they were.

684
01:00:08,160 --> 01:00:10,520
Because everything in life was temporary.

685
01:00:11,200 --> 01:00:12,360
The only thing that lasted...

686
01:00:13,640 --> 01:00:14,640
was love.

687
01:00:18,880 --> 01:00:20,360
What happened to the pearl necklace?

688
01:00:20,560 --> 01:00:21,920
She should have at least found it.

689
01:00:27,040 --> 01:00:28,400
She found it, she found it, relax.

690
01:00:30,360 --> 01:00:33,240
Every time she looked at that pearl,
she remembered her husband's words.

691
01:00:37,600 --> 01:00:38,600
The husband and wife...

692
01:00:39,320 --> 01:00:40,960
lived happily...

693
01:00:41,880 --> 01:00:43,000
for the rest of their lives.

694
01:00:47,520 --> 01:00:48,520
Happy ending.

695
01:00:49,960 --> 01:00:51,280
Very happy indeed.

696
01:01:15,960 --> 01:01:17,040
Zehra. My wifey.

697
01:01:17,880 --> 01:01:19,240
Aren't you going to eat any bread?

698
01:01:19,360 --> 01:01:20,360
I'm on a diet.

699
01:01:21,960 --> 01:01:22,960
Ah, right.

700
01:01:28,000 --> 01:01:29,720
-Pickles? -I don't want any, Berat!

701
01:01:46,240 --> 01:01:47,240
Zehra?

702
01:01:50,520 --> 01:01:53,080
We sinned against you, my girl, forgive us.

703
01:01:54,800 --> 01:01:59,120
We were affected by previous
events and passed judgment.

704
01:01:59,520 --> 01:02:00,880
We were prejudiced.

705
01:02:01,720 --> 01:02:03,440
But of course, this is wrong...

706
01:02:05,200 --> 01:02:06,360
We made a mistake.

707
01:02:07,160 --> 01:02:11,320
But you do the right thing. Forgive us.

708
01:02:13,920 --> 01:02:14,920
Yes, Zehra.

709
01:02:15,840 --> 01:02:16,840
I'm sorry.

710
01:02:17,840 --> 01:02:18,840
We did you wrong.

711
01:02:20,840 --> 01:02:22,120
We are genuinely very sorry.

712
01:02:32,600 --> 01:02:33,760
We apologize.

713
01:02:43,920 --> 01:02:45,520
It's good that you realize your mistake.

714
01:02:46,280 --> 01:02:48,240
I hope you won't do things
like this from now on.

715
01:02:49,080 --> 01:02:50,160
I mean, if we are a family,

716
01:02:50,760 --> 01:02:52,920
things don't work out if
only one side is forgiving...

717
01:02:56,720 --> 01:03:00,040
Daughter, this is exactly
what being a family requires.

718
01:03:00,880 --> 01:03:03,560
We're all sitting together, eating dinner.

719
01:03:25,080 --> 01:03:28,200
Let this be my belated wedding gift to you.

720
01:03:33,720 --> 01:03:34,720
Here, take it.

721
01:03:37,840 --> 01:03:40,320
I wish I could do more, but...

722
01:03:42,080 --> 01:03:44,440
this is the best I can do for now.

723
01:03:45,880 --> 01:03:48,000
I can give you something
better too, God willing.

724
01:03:49,680 --> 01:03:50,800
Thank you, Mother Binnaz.

725
01:03:52,240 --> 01:03:54,600
But what I really need
isn't a gift, it's a room.

726
01:03:56,280 --> 01:03:58,120
I keep saying it, but nobody hears me.

727
01:03:58,480 --> 01:03:59,640
We can't fit in there.

728
01:04:01,520 --> 01:04:02,600
You've started again.

729
01:04:04,720 --> 01:04:07,600
All you keep harping on
about is a room, a room.

730
01:04:08,520 --> 01:04:10,120
We told you we'd figure it out.

731
01:04:14,920 --> 01:04:15,920
Move into my room.

732
01:04:23,400 --> 01:04:25,720
Yes. You can settle into my room.

733
01:04:26,760 --> 01:04:28,520
My room feels too big for me anyway.

734
01:04:29,040 --> 01:04:31,440
I'll move into the
little room by the storage.

735
01:04:32,240 --> 01:04:33,440
You are newlyweds.

736
01:04:34,160 --> 01:04:36,600
Let this be my wedding gift to you.

737
01:04:40,200 --> 01:04:43,640
Malik, shouldn't we have talked
about this between us first!

738
01:04:43,800 --> 01:04:45,480
Çiçek, they are newlyweds.

739
01:04:48,400 --> 01:04:50,120
From the groom's brother-in-law...

740
01:04:51,840 --> 01:04:52,840
A room.

741
01:04:54,920 --> 01:04:55,920
Bless you, man!

742
01:04:56,480 --> 01:04:58,600
- My brother.
- You're welcome, brother-in-law.

743
01:04:58,800 --> 01:05:00,120
-Brother-in-law? -Brother-in-law.

744
01:05:00,680 --> 01:05:01,680
I like the sound of that.

745
01:05:01,960 --> 01:05:04,720
-I mean, son... -You're amazing, Malik.

746
01:05:05,080 --> 01:05:07,280
Honestly, it was the surprise of the day!

747
01:05:08,080 --> 01:05:10,360
Don't mention it. As
long as you guys are happy.

748
01:05:12,320 --> 01:05:14,800
You are a wonderful guy. Truly.

749
01:05:16,360 --> 01:05:18,720
Haven't I been saying this
from the very beginning?

750
01:05:19,240 --> 01:05:21,600
That Malik is a magnificent guy? Huh?

751
01:05:21,920 --> 01:05:24,800
Didn't I say it? You
haven't disappointed me once.

752
01:05:26,000 --> 01:05:28,640
You looked a bit surprised
when throwing that punch, though.

753
01:05:33,200 --> 01:05:35,520
Forget about all that now.

754
01:05:35,840 --> 01:05:37,760
My hand slipped that day, I mean... well...

755
01:05:38,560 --> 01:05:39,680
Let's just say it's past.

756
01:05:39,880 --> 01:05:41,320
-Let's say that, then. -There we go.

757
01:05:41,480 --> 01:05:43,160
-Alright then. -Something like that.

758
01:05:44,920 --> 01:05:45,920
So?

759
01:05:47,640 --> 01:05:51,160
When will you empty out
the room? I'll help you.

760
01:05:51,520 --> 01:05:54,200
The sooner, the better, right?

761
01:05:54,360 --> 01:05:55,360
Of course.

762
01:05:55,720 --> 01:05:58,240
Okay, we'll get it done
at the first opportunity.

763
01:06:23,720 --> 01:06:24,880
Eylül...

764
01:06:29,680 --> 01:06:30,680
Eylül...

765
01:06:32,680 --> 01:06:33,680
Eylül...

766
01:06:34,520 --> 01:06:35,520
Eylül...

767
01:06:36,200 --> 01:06:37,200
Eylül...

768
01:06:43,680 --> 01:06:44,680
Eylül!

769
01:06:46,440 --> 01:06:47,440
Mercan...

770
01:06:53,640 --> 01:06:54,640
Ateş.

771
01:06:55,240 --> 01:06:56,040
Calm down.

772
01:06:56,200 --> 01:06:57,600
Ateş... I...

773
01:07:04,160 --> 01:07:06,000
-Ateş... Ateş, I... -It's okay.

774
01:07:06,120 --> 01:07:07,440
It's over. I'm right here...

775
01:07:08,080 --> 01:07:09,080
It's over.

776
01:07:11,960 --> 01:07:13,840
I saw Eylül in my dream.

777
01:07:17,720 --> 01:07:19,160
Someone was going to hurt her...

778
01:07:20,480 --> 01:07:22,280
I was running to stop it.

779
01:07:22,880 --> 01:07:24,776
But after a certain point,
I couldn't see Eylül...

780
01:07:24,800 --> 01:07:26,520
She kept disappearing down a dark street...

781
01:07:27,320 --> 01:07:29,160
I just couldn't reach her.

782
01:07:30,160 --> 01:07:32,080
I couldn't hold her hand and save her!

783
01:07:33,560 --> 01:07:35,720
I couldn't help her!

784
01:07:36,760 --> 01:07:37,760
It's okay.

785
01:07:38,480 --> 01:07:39,760
It's over. It was just a dream.

786
01:07:40,360 --> 01:07:42,560
You shouldn't be thinking
about these things right now.

787
01:07:43,360 --> 01:07:44,360
Look...

788
01:07:44,440 --> 01:07:45,680
I am by your side. It's over.

789
01:07:51,480 --> 01:07:53,480
Okay. I feel better.

790
01:07:54,600 --> 01:07:55,920
Everything is so fresh still.

791
01:07:56,920 --> 01:07:57,920
It will pass.

792
01:07:58,040 --> 01:07:59,040
It will pass.

793
01:07:59,960 --> 01:08:00,960
It will pass.

794
01:08:04,560 --> 01:08:05,560
You...

795
01:08:06,880 --> 01:08:10,080
Despite everything you went
through, you didn't choose to be bad.

796
01:08:13,640 --> 01:08:15,280
You didn't lose your sense of justice...

797
01:08:23,200 --> 01:08:25,080
You did the hardest thing, Ateş.

798
01:08:27,200 --> 01:08:28,920
You remained pure in all that darkness.

799
01:08:37,080 --> 01:08:38,600
Please hug me.

800
01:08:39,920 --> 01:08:41,320
Hug me tight.

801
01:08:42,440 --> 01:08:44,160
Like you're never going to let go.

802
01:09:50,560 --> 01:09:53,800
Even just thinking about what
you lived through feels heavy to me.

803
01:09:55,160 --> 01:09:57,320
Your whole life has
been spent being tested.

804
01:09:58,720 --> 01:10:00,240
Now, I am not a source of happiness,

805
01:10:00,840 --> 01:10:02,320
but a new test for you.

806
01:10:08,080 --> 01:10:09,640
And a massive test at that.

807
01:10:11,640 --> 01:10:13,120
Everything you've held onto so far,

808
01:10:14,160 --> 01:10:17,160
everything that ties you to life...
you're being forced to give it all up

809
01:10:17,200 --> 01:10:18,360
just to hold my hand.

810
01:10:20,320 --> 01:10:21,320
I can't let this happen.

811
01:11:02,080 --> 01:11:03,320
Did you have a nightmare again?

812
01:11:05,720 --> 01:11:06,720
No.

813
01:11:09,640 --> 01:11:11,680
I just had a beautiful dream...

814
01:11:15,240 --> 01:11:16,880
But it was time for me to wake up.

815
01:11:23,520 --> 01:11:25,360
I love you so much, you know that, right?

816
01:11:31,120 --> 01:11:32,400
I love you very much too.

817
01:12:08,040 --> 01:12:09,080
The air is wonderful.

818
01:12:22,520 --> 01:12:24,560
It's cold out, go back inside now.

819
01:12:25,040 --> 01:12:27,520
You need to rest. And you
didn't even put anything warm on.

820
01:12:28,400 --> 01:12:30,200
It's fine like this. I'm not going in.

821
01:12:31,760 --> 01:12:32,840
I told you to go inside.

822
01:12:35,960 --> 01:12:37,560
You've started giving orders again.

823
01:12:38,680 --> 01:12:40,120
And I told you I am not going in.

824
01:12:41,640 --> 01:12:44,320
I think we can declare right
now that you've lost the bet.

825
01:12:47,040 --> 01:12:50,040
What were you going
to ask for when you won?

826
01:13:50,080 --> 01:13:51,720
While I wanted to be your heaven...

827
01:13:53,160 --> 01:13:54,560
I left you in purgatory...

828
01:13:56,600 --> 01:13:57,720
Our story...

829
01:13:58,560 --> 01:14:00,320
was two flames burning each other to ashes.

830
01:14:02,480 --> 01:14:04,960
If my leaving is the only
wall that will protect you,

831
01:14:05,880 --> 01:14:08,120
I am willing to live
with an endless longing.

832
01:14:09,880 --> 01:14:12,440
Because your peace matters
more than my presence.

833
01:14:16,080 --> 01:14:19,000
I am giving you up, for you.

834
01:15:23,520 --> 01:15:25,120
Let's do something together today.

835
01:15:26,240 --> 01:15:30,560
Let's go out, spend the
whole day alone together.

836
01:15:31,600 --> 01:15:34,800
No, you haven't recovered
yet. You need to rest.

837
01:15:37,680 --> 01:15:41,680
Besides, I remind you,
you lost the bet on purpose.

838
01:15:42,880 --> 01:15:45,200
Come on... Don't disappoint me.

839
01:15:46,520 --> 01:15:48,320
We'll spend some time together.

840
01:15:49,120 --> 01:15:50,640
I feel fine.

841
01:15:51,560 --> 01:15:53,040
We're together at home too, Mercan...

842
01:15:53,640 --> 01:15:54,680
I don't want to upset you.

843
01:15:56,560 --> 01:15:58,120
-But outside... -Shh.

844
01:16:02,040 --> 01:16:05,400
I want to spend today alone with you.

845
01:16:06,560 --> 01:16:08,800
To do things we couldn't do before...

846
01:16:10,080 --> 01:16:14,400
I want to laugh a little, walk a little…

847
01:16:15,000 --> 01:16:16,000
That's all.

848
01:16:17,040 --> 01:16:18,120
No more, no less.

849
01:16:19,840 --> 01:16:20,840
Okay…

850
01:16:21,760 --> 01:16:23,200
I'm at your service all day.

851
01:16:23,600 --> 01:16:25,280
We'll do whatever you want.

852
01:16:26,080 --> 01:16:27,520
Come on, get ready. We're going out.

853
01:16:29,680 --> 01:16:30,840
Thank you…

854
01:16:43,200 --> 01:16:45,720
Malik's room is quite big too, Berat.

855
01:16:45,960 --> 01:16:47,400
We'd be much more comfortable there…

856
01:16:48,000 --> 01:16:49,000
Yes.

857
01:16:49,680 --> 01:16:52,320
It was good of him to leave it to us.

858
01:16:52,520 --> 01:16:55,920
Of course he would... It's not like we're
going to stay cooped up in that tiny room!

859
01:16:57,040 --> 01:16:58,440
Oh, right. Right.

860
01:16:59,440 --> 01:17:03,000
We'll furnish the room
according to your taste. Okay?

861
01:17:03,560 --> 01:17:06,360
But I don't want any bedroom
set other than the one I liked.

862
01:17:06,840 --> 01:17:09,880
We'll get whatever you want, my wife.

863
01:17:11,080 --> 01:17:12,960
My sweetheart. Don't you worry.

864
01:17:14,120 --> 01:17:15,120
In fact...

865
01:17:16,320 --> 01:17:20,040
We haven't been able to be
alone since we got married.

866
01:17:20,840 --> 01:17:22,400
Have we? I mean...

867
01:17:23,240 --> 01:17:27,080
How nice it is to finally
have a room of our own.

868
01:17:28,480 --> 01:17:31,760
After everything we've been through these
days, that's what you're thinking about?

869
01:17:32,160 --> 01:17:34,520
Of course I'm thinking about
it, my girl... Of course.

870
01:17:41,720 --> 01:17:43,120
Oh my God!

871
01:17:43,560 --> 01:17:46,680
Thank goodness we'll finally
have a room of our own.

872
01:17:46,720 --> 01:17:47,720
Thank goodness.

873
01:17:48,080 --> 01:17:50,880
I'm sorry, madam, but
these are our circumstances.

874
01:17:51,040 --> 01:17:53,480
If you didn't want this, you
shouldn't have gotten married...

875
01:17:54,600 --> 01:17:57,560
What do you want? For us to leave
the house so you won't be uncomfortable?

876
01:17:59,800 --> 01:18:02,280
Çiçek! That's not nice!

877
01:18:03,400 --> 01:18:04,920
Brother, don't you see?

878
01:18:05,080 --> 01:18:07,320
She's practically going to
kick us out of our own house.

879
01:18:13,320 --> 01:18:14,320
Çiçek!

880
01:18:15,520 --> 01:18:17,840
Okay, the woman didn't say anything.

881
01:18:18,400 --> 01:18:23,480
You want to know what I think? I
think you two will get along great.

882
01:18:24,160 --> 01:18:26,880
You'll make a great pair.

883
01:18:27,520 --> 01:18:28,640
-Hmm... -Don't dwell on it.

884
01:18:33,600 --> 01:18:35,120
She always dwells on things like this.

885
01:18:36,680 --> 01:18:38,840
My dear wife. Please.

886
01:18:40,640 --> 01:18:42,280
Maybe we shouldn't dwell on it?

887
01:18:43,840 --> 01:18:47,080
Oh! You could have just fainted, brother!

888
01:18:48,600 --> 01:18:50,080
Çiçek! Dear.

889
01:18:53,560 --> 01:18:57,760
My dear wife. Shall we go to our room now?

890
01:18:59,560 --> 01:19:00,560
Let's go, shall we?

891
01:19:00,960 --> 01:19:03,120
Okay. Let's go, my love.

892
01:19:03,360 --> 01:19:04,680
-Let's go. -My dear husband.

893
01:19:05,000 --> 01:19:06,000
Let's go.

894
01:19:11,040 --> 01:19:12,040
Come, my wife.

895
01:19:12,200 --> 01:19:13,200
My strong husband.

896
01:19:13,720 --> 01:19:14,720
Let's go to our new room.

897
01:19:20,680 --> 01:19:22,280
She's turned into a complete lapdog.

898
01:19:22,560 --> 01:19:24,160
But when it comes to us, she's all talk.

899
01:19:24,600 --> 01:19:25,720
Hey, oh my God.

900
01:19:28,440 --> 01:19:29,480
Thank you very much.

901
01:19:30,960 --> 01:19:31,960
However...

902
01:19:32,680 --> 01:19:34,480
No one should know about this for now…

903
01:19:36,200 --> 01:19:38,600
Of course, you can send it to me via email…

904
01:19:42,600 --> 01:19:43,600
We'll be in touch.

905
01:19:44,400 --> 01:19:45,400
See you, dear.

906
01:19:47,520 --> 01:19:48,520
Who were you talking to?

907
01:19:49,600 --> 01:19:52,680
Demet… She was wondering how I was.

908
01:19:57,320 --> 01:20:00,840
Your face is flushed. If you don't
feel well, we don't have to go out.

909
01:20:01,200 --> 01:20:02,200
No, no.

910
01:20:02,960 --> 01:20:06,160
It's very hot in here,
that's why my face is flushed.

911
01:20:07,560 --> 01:20:09,200
Okay. Promise me.

912
01:20:10,200 --> 01:20:11,960
When you get tired, we'll come back.

913
01:20:12,600 --> 01:20:13,600
Promise.

914
01:20:20,800 --> 01:20:21,800
You had it repaired.

915
01:20:24,560 --> 01:20:25,560
Yes.

916
01:20:27,680 --> 01:20:29,320
But I'll give it to you on one condition.

917
01:20:32,440 --> 01:20:34,880
You have to promise you'll
never take it off your neck again.

918
01:21:17,280 --> 01:21:18,360
I'll be waiting downstairs.

919
01:21:20,880 --> 01:21:23,640
Dress warmly accordingly.
Otherwise we'll come right back.

920
01:21:24,560 --> 01:21:25,560
Okay.

921
01:22:03,120 --> 01:22:04,920
Why didn't Cemal come to breakfast?

922
01:22:05,640 --> 01:22:06,640
How should I know…

923
01:22:07,320 --> 01:22:09,000
He's been acting strange lately too.

924
01:22:10,000 --> 01:22:11,240
Who does he think he is…

925
01:22:12,080 --> 01:22:14,120
He's just someone running Ateş's errands.

926
01:22:14,960 --> 01:22:16,960
Like he's our boss.

927
01:22:17,960 --> 01:22:19,400
Girl, you've completely lost it.

928
01:22:20,160 --> 01:22:21,240
What's your problem?

929
01:22:22,040 --> 01:22:24,080
Everyone else is done,
now you're picking on Cemal?

930
01:22:26,720 --> 01:22:29,320
I'm tired of giving you advice.

931
01:22:30,160 --> 01:22:31,320
Then don't.

932
01:22:32,040 --> 01:22:33,040
What am I even doing?

933
01:22:34,680 --> 01:22:36,000
You want to know something?

934
01:22:36,680 --> 01:22:38,920
Everyone has forgotten why we came here.

935
01:22:39,480 --> 01:22:42,280
You included. I'm the only
one who hasn't forgotten.

936
01:22:43,400 --> 01:22:45,280
Because of you, you idiot!

937
01:22:46,120 --> 01:22:48,240
You didn't wait, even
when Ateş kept saying wait!

938
01:22:48,920 --> 01:22:52,120
Look, when Mercan got sick,
their relationship improved.

939
01:22:52,400 --> 01:22:53,880
Don't you use your head at all?

940
01:22:54,680 --> 01:22:56,280
Your anger is hurting us.

941
01:22:56,720 --> 01:22:57,920
Get a grip.

942
01:22:58,800 --> 01:23:02,200
As long as you act so foolishly,
we won't be able to achieve anything.

943
01:23:03,000 --> 01:23:04,000
Enough already!

944
01:23:04,400 --> 01:23:06,120
I'm tired of you constantly criticizing me!

945
01:23:22,520 --> 01:23:23,520
Good morning.

946
01:23:23,960 --> 01:23:24,960
Good morning, my son.

947
01:23:26,400 --> 01:23:27,480
You went to the hospital?

948
01:23:28,160 --> 01:23:29,160
Is there a problem?

949
01:23:31,800 --> 01:23:32,800
Me?

950
01:23:33,360 --> 01:23:34,920
There was a hospital bill in your name?

951
01:23:38,880 --> 01:23:39,880
Oh.

952
01:23:41,040 --> 01:23:43,000
I must have caught a bit of a cold.

953
01:23:43,560 --> 01:23:46,240
Since I was there, I thought
I'd get everything checked.

954
01:23:47,600 --> 01:23:50,120
If you want, we can take
you to a better hospital?

955
01:23:51,800 --> 01:23:52,800
No, son.

956
01:23:53,440 --> 01:23:54,440
I'm fine.

957
01:23:54,560 --> 01:23:55,880
Thank you, my brave boy.

958
01:24:05,000 --> 01:24:06,320
I need to be careful.

959
01:24:07,240 --> 01:24:08,560
Ateş must not suspect anything.

960
01:24:23,640 --> 01:24:24,640
Ateş.

961
01:24:26,360 --> 01:24:27,360
How is Mercan?

962
01:24:28,840 --> 01:24:29,840
Better…

963
01:24:30,760 --> 01:24:32,520
We'll walk a bit, she
wanted some fresh air.

964
01:24:33,600 --> 01:24:34,600
That'll be good.

965
01:24:35,760 --> 01:24:38,400
This place is starting
to get to me too now.

966
01:24:39,960 --> 01:24:41,440
What happened affected Mercan deeply.

967
01:24:43,400 --> 01:24:45,200
She should never have learned this truth.

968
01:24:45,560 --> 01:24:46,960
It's normal for her to be affected.

969
01:24:49,480 --> 01:24:51,600
Evil is so ordinary for Haydar…

970
01:24:53,600 --> 01:24:55,720
He doesn't even care about
the destruction he causes.

971
01:24:59,360 --> 01:25:00,840
What are we going to do about Haydar?

972
01:25:03,240 --> 01:25:04,440
He'll stay.

973
01:25:12,040 --> 01:25:13,360
Is it okay, Ateş Bey?

974
01:25:14,440 --> 01:25:16,360
I mean... It's nice.

975
01:25:17,800 --> 01:25:19,280
Actually, you could have worn gloves.

976
01:25:20,840 --> 01:25:23,520
I wanted to get some air.

977
01:25:24,520 --> 01:25:26,040
If this goes on, I'll suffocate.

978
01:25:26,120 --> 01:25:27,520
I've turned into a snowman.

979
01:25:28,440 --> 01:25:31,200
If you want to go to the
shore, you have to do as I say.

980
01:25:37,960 --> 01:25:40,800
Cemal, can you take a short video?

981
01:25:41,920 --> 01:25:44,520
Of course, sure, but
I'm not very good at it.

982
01:25:44,880 --> 01:25:46,000
What kind of video is this?

983
01:25:46,320 --> 01:25:47,720
Look at the camera.

984
01:25:50,840 --> 01:25:51,840
Are you recording?

985
01:25:54,280 --> 01:25:56,880
We're just going to make a quick
stop at the poles and come back.

986
01:25:59,200 --> 01:26:01,560
If I don't evaporate thanks
to my dear husband, of course…

987
01:26:20,120 --> 01:26:21,120
Okay.

988
01:26:22,080 --> 01:26:23,080
Thank you.

989
01:26:23,560 --> 01:26:24,560
You're welcome.

990
01:26:25,000 --> 01:26:27,000
Since you managed to get out, enjoy it.

991
01:26:27,600 --> 01:26:28,880
I'll get going. Have a good day.

992
01:26:29,480 --> 01:26:30,480
Thanks.

993
01:26:31,040 --> 01:26:32,040
Alright, come on...

994
01:26:33,640 --> 01:26:35,400
Whoa! The scarf stays around your neck.

995
01:26:36,040 --> 01:26:37,720
But I'm so suffocated.

996
01:26:38,320 --> 01:26:40,200
We're getting in the car anyway.

997
01:26:40,400 --> 01:26:42,040
-I promise... -Come on, Mercan.

998
01:27:05,440 --> 01:27:07,840
Promise, I'll put it on
when we get out of the car.

999
01:27:09,840 --> 01:27:11,160
Oh, patience!

1000
01:27:33,720 --> 01:27:34,720
Well done!

1001
01:27:34,880 --> 01:27:36,160
Enjoy your meal.

1002
01:27:38,360 --> 01:27:40,880
I wish you hadn't given
your room to Zehra, Malik.

1003
01:27:43,600 --> 01:27:45,440
I didn't give the room to Zehra.

1004
01:27:46,520 --> 01:27:47,680
I gave it to Berat and Zehra.

1005
01:27:48,000 --> 01:27:50,239
Still, I wish you hadn't.

1006
01:27:50,240 --> 01:27:52,600
Zehra is so insufferably full of herself.

1007
01:27:55,280 --> 01:27:58,760
But Çiçek, they're
newlyweds. They have a point.

1008
01:27:59,600 --> 01:28:01,480
If it were you, you'd want it too.

1009
01:28:04,800 --> 01:28:05,800
I...

1010
01:28:08,680 --> 01:28:10,320
I don't desire anything.

1011
01:28:10,440 --> 01:28:12,360
As long as we're together, Malik.

1012
01:28:17,200 --> 01:28:19,000
I know, my love. I know.

1013
01:28:19,920 --> 01:28:21,160
That's why I love you so much.

1014
01:28:22,120 --> 01:28:24,120
You love me for who I am.

1015
01:28:26,680 --> 01:28:30,200
Our humble home, our table,

1016
01:28:30,920 --> 01:28:32,896
our meals... they must have
seemed strange to you at first.

1017
01:28:32,920 --> 01:28:34,440
And we also serve.

1018
01:28:37,120 --> 01:28:38,120
I never found it strange.

1019
01:28:39,440 --> 01:28:40,480
In fact, I loved it.

1020
01:28:43,760 --> 01:28:45,440
My father works day and night.

1021
01:28:46,400 --> 01:28:47,720
He barely stops by home properly.

1022
01:28:48,800 --> 01:28:51,880
My mother is constantly
traveling or hosting guests.

1023
01:28:53,000 --> 01:28:56,080
We don't spend much time
together as a family like you do.

1024
01:28:58,560 --> 01:29:00,160
Your mother Binnaz's table is different.

1025
01:29:00,880 --> 01:29:03,360
It's always abundant, full
of conversation, cheerful…

1026
01:29:05,400 --> 01:29:08,159
Even if you fight, you still
sit at the table together.

1027
01:29:08,160 --> 01:29:12,440
You share your troubles, you
solve your problems together.

1028
01:29:15,360 --> 01:29:16,360
Çiçek...

1029
01:29:18,000 --> 01:29:20,840
I loved you, I loved your family.

1030
01:29:26,360 --> 01:29:30,000
Now it's not just my family,
it's our family, Malik.

1031
01:29:30,680 --> 01:29:32,680
You became a part of the family too.

1032
01:30:06,440 --> 01:30:09,040
I saw you with Ateş and
Mercan a little while ago…

1033
01:30:10,360 --> 01:30:13,000
May God increase your affection,
you seemed very cheerful.

1034
01:30:16,520 --> 01:30:17,880
What do you want, Aslı?

1035
01:30:20,160 --> 01:30:21,840
Why are you being mean to me, Cemal?

1036
01:30:22,240 --> 01:30:24,800
I think you know the reason very well.

1037
01:30:25,680 --> 01:30:27,480
You know very well why…

1038
01:30:28,160 --> 01:30:30,120
You betrayed Ateş.

1039
01:30:32,440 --> 01:30:34,480
We talked about this and
closed the subject, Cemal.

1040
01:30:35,040 --> 01:30:36,440
Why are you dragging it out?

1041
01:30:37,200 --> 01:30:39,400
You and Ateş betrayed me too!

1042
01:30:40,360 --> 01:30:43,240
You turned your backs on
me and sided with Mercan!

1043
01:30:44,160 --> 01:30:46,960
I know very well what
you're trying to do now.

1044
01:30:47,600 --> 01:30:50,320
Don't try to justify
yourself by blaming us.

1045
01:30:50,800 --> 01:30:54,920
I was willing to help you
despite everything you did.

1046
01:30:55,600 --> 01:30:56,600
What did you do?

1047
01:30:56,920 --> 01:30:58,000
You betrayed us.

1048
01:31:00,520 --> 01:31:03,200
Because of you, my mind
is constantly in turmoil.

1049
01:31:04,840 --> 01:31:06,720
You're making such a
big deal out of it, Cemal!

1050
01:31:07,640 --> 01:31:09,680
If you were going to throw
it in my face like this,

1051
01:31:09,920 --> 01:31:11,960
I wish you had never kept
quiet in the first place.

1052
01:31:15,720 --> 01:31:16,760
No, you don't understand.

1053
01:31:17,440 --> 01:31:18,760
And you never will...

1054
01:31:20,080 --> 01:31:21,640
Do you want to know why I stayed quiet?

1055
01:31:21,880 --> 01:31:23,440
Do you want to know why I kept silent?

1056
01:31:24,560 --> 01:31:26,240
I stayed quiet because...

1057
01:31:34,160 --> 01:31:37,240
Because I stayed quiet thinking
we could never be like before again.

1058
01:31:37,640 --> 01:31:41,280
I was afraid that if Ateş found
out, we couldn't be like we used to be.

1059
01:31:43,280 --> 01:31:46,600
Ateş would get angry,
shout, then fall silent.

1060
01:31:47,360 --> 01:31:48,840
He would never turn his back on us.

1061
01:31:54,280 --> 01:31:55,480
It's not that simple.

1062
01:31:59,040 --> 01:32:02,080
This isn't like you getting angry at
Mercan and telling her the truth, Aslı.

1063
01:32:04,600 --> 01:32:06,040
Then keep your mouth shut.

1064
01:32:07,160 --> 01:32:08,520
After all, you're my accomplice.

1065
01:32:17,280 --> 01:32:18,640
This is absolutely unbearable now.

1066
01:32:38,640 --> 01:32:40,000
There was no need!

1067
01:32:40,680 --> 01:32:41,920
I could have crossed by myself.

1068
01:32:50,040 --> 01:32:51,160
Come, let's sit for a while.

1069
01:32:51,880 --> 01:32:53,600
We've been walking for a while, rest a bit.

1070
01:32:54,160 --> 01:32:57,160
Ateş, don't exaggerate,
I'm not that delicate.

1071
01:32:59,600 --> 01:33:00,640
To me, you are delicate.

1072
01:33:01,600 --> 01:33:03,320
I want to wrap you in cotton wool and...

1073
01:33:04,080 --> 01:33:06,000
hide you in the tower of my castle.

1074
01:33:11,520 --> 01:33:12,520
Why did you laugh?

1075
01:33:12,600 --> 01:33:13,600
I'm very serious.

1076
01:33:14,160 --> 01:33:15,160
And...

1077
01:33:15,280 --> 01:33:17,240
Aren't I your grumpy prince?

1078
01:33:18,200 --> 01:33:19,200
You are.

1079
01:33:19,800 --> 01:33:21,880
Well, don't princes have castles?

1080
01:33:23,520 --> 01:33:24,520
They do, but...

1081
01:33:25,120 --> 01:33:26,880
A castle like that...

1082
01:33:27,760 --> 01:33:29,280
Wouldn't life be very boring?

1083
01:33:30,080 --> 01:33:31,080
No.

1084
01:33:32,920 --> 01:33:34,800
Why would it be boring
as long as I'm with you?

1085
01:33:38,480 --> 01:33:39,720
I would never get bored either.

1086
01:33:52,200 --> 01:33:53,240
It's very cold…

1087
01:33:53,960 --> 01:33:54,960
Don't get cold.

1088
01:34:02,000 --> 01:34:03,240
We should come here more often.

1089
01:34:04,200 --> 01:34:05,800
Okay… we'll come.

1090
01:34:26,640 --> 01:34:28,120
-Come on, smile… -Okay.

1091
01:34:44,160 --> 01:34:45,160
Alright, come on.

1092
01:34:45,760 --> 01:34:46,800
Let's walk a little more.

1093
01:34:47,600 --> 01:34:48,760
Come here!

1094
01:35:28,680 --> 01:35:29,760
Don't be naughty.

1095
01:36:12,400 --> 01:36:13,760
Come Binnaz, come.

1096
01:36:25,120 --> 01:36:27,320
Ms Nermin, I brought you coffee.

1097
01:36:29,440 --> 01:36:32,040
Binnaz... Binnaz.

1098
01:36:33,920 --> 01:36:35,880
Binnaz, we didn't deserve this…

1099
01:36:37,520 --> 01:36:39,200
We didn't deserve to fall apart like this.

1100
01:36:44,280 --> 01:36:45,320
Imagine a house…

1101
01:36:47,400 --> 01:36:50,120
Everyone is inside, but
no one can touch each other.

1102
01:36:52,560 --> 01:36:53,560
I...

1103
01:36:54,840 --> 01:36:56,560
I... I can't take it anymore.

1104
01:37:00,920 --> 01:37:03,080
Time heals everything, Ms Nermin.

1105
01:37:04,360 --> 01:37:06,280
You'll see, you'll get better with time.

1106
01:37:08,080 --> 01:37:09,600
All of you will get better.

1107
01:37:12,920 --> 01:37:15,080
Can the pain of a child
be forgotten, Binnaz?

1108
01:37:18,000 --> 01:37:22,680
Both of my children fell
apart right in front of my eyes.

1109
01:37:24,560 --> 01:37:25,560
My son died.

1110
01:37:27,240 --> 01:37:28,720
And look at the state of my daughter.

1111
01:37:33,600 --> 01:37:35,560
Why did this happen to us?

1112
01:37:40,520 --> 01:37:43,800
God gives the hardship, and He gives
the patience to bear it, Ms Nermin.

1113
01:37:47,000 --> 01:37:48,000
Don't you worry.

1114
01:37:50,160 --> 01:37:51,880
God is great, these days will pass too.

1115
01:37:55,000 --> 01:37:56,800
Nothing will be the same again, Binnaz.

1116
01:37:59,240 --> 01:38:00,880
Nothing will get better.

1117
01:38:53,920 --> 01:38:56,000
Be careful… don't get wet,
the weather is very cold.

1118
01:38:56,880 --> 01:38:57,880
It'll be fine.

1119
01:38:59,000 --> 01:39:00,560
I'll just put my hand in the water.

1120
01:39:18,160 --> 01:39:19,160
Stop, what are you doing!

1121
01:39:21,040 --> 01:39:22,040
Mercan, stop!

1122
01:39:23,160 --> 01:39:24,160
I said stop!

1123
01:39:35,040 --> 01:39:37,976
Thank goodness the weather is cold, or I
would have thrown you into the sea just now.

1124
01:39:38,000 --> 01:39:39,696
Then you'd see what
getting wet really means.

1125
01:39:39,720 --> 01:39:41,320
I did it knowing that.

1126
01:39:42,040 --> 01:39:43,880
Come on, come on, stop whining…

1127
01:39:44,520 --> 01:39:45,520
It's so nice though...

1128
01:39:46,440 --> 01:39:47,880
Guilty and strong.

1129
01:39:52,920 --> 01:39:54,440
Stop complaining now.

1130
01:39:55,360 --> 01:39:56,960
Since we're by the sea...

1131
01:39:58,200 --> 01:39:59,400
Shall we play skipping stones?

1132
01:40:00,400 --> 01:40:03,240
The loser carries the winner on their back.

1133
01:40:03,960 --> 01:40:08,080
I'm sick, it'll be nice
if you carry me to the car.

1134
01:40:08,760 --> 01:40:10,800
Ah, so you're that sure you'll win.

1135
01:40:15,120 --> 01:40:16,920
Yes. Deal?

1136
01:40:18,040 --> 01:40:19,120
Deal…

1137
01:40:19,720 --> 01:40:23,080
But no sulking or crying afterwards.

1138
01:40:23,920 --> 01:40:26,920
No problem, since I'm going to win anyway.

1139
01:40:59,120 --> 01:41:01,000
There should be a trace
of us in this building.

1140
01:41:01,480 --> 01:41:02,480
A line...

1141
01:41:02,960 --> 01:41:04,640
Maybe a stone sitting askew.

1142
01:41:05,920 --> 01:41:07,680
A feeling of us in its own world.

1143
01:41:09,280 --> 01:41:10,600
It will stand there, firm.

1144
01:41:14,400 --> 01:41:15,480
I'm keeping this.

1145
01:41:17,280 --> 01:41:19,200
Somewhere, there will
always be a stone from us.

1146
01:41:20,440 --> 01:41:21,600
Belonging only to us two.

1147
01:41:28,120 --> 01:41:29,440
Alright then, we're starting.

1148
01:41:30,400 --> 01:41:32,000
If you still want to continue, that is?

1149
01:41:33,920 --> 01:41:35,800
Am I the type to go back on my word?

1150
01:41:41,960 --> 01:41:42,960
No, you're not…

1151
01:41:50,720 --> 01:41:52,720
Don't try to distract me, young lady.

1152
01:41:53,680 --> 01:41:55,640
Don't let yourself be
distracted then, young sir.

1153
01:42:25,440 --> 01:42:26,440
You cheated!

1154
01:42:26,800 --> 01:42:27,800
It's your fault.

1155
01:42:28,760 --> 01:42:30,000
You deliberately distracted me.

1156
01:42:31,360 --> 01:42:32,960
You shouldn't have fallen into the trap.

1157
01:42:37,000 --> 01:42:38,440
It wasn't a fair match.

1158
01:42:39,680 --> 01:42:42,520
You know my attention
wanders when you're near me.

1159
01:42:44,400 --> 01:42:45,400
Don't complain.

1160
01:42:46,920 --> 01:42:48,960
Admitting defeat is sportsmanship.

1161
01:42:49,960 --> 01:42:52,720
You promised, you'll carry me.

1162
01:43:04,360 --> 01:43:06,760
Ateş! Put me down! We're going to fall.

1163
01:44:25,360 --> 01:44:26,360
Come on, get up.

1164
01:44:28,560 --> 01:44:29,720
We're leaving.

1165
01:44:32,960 --> 01:44:34,760
I'll carry you on my back to the car.

1166
01:44:35,120 --> 01:44:37,280
No need, I was teasing you.

1167
01:44:37,480 --> 01:44:39,040
No way. A promise is a promise.

1168
01:45:15,080 --> 01:45:16,080
Hello?

1169
01:45:16,440 --> 01:45:18,320
Hello Ateş Bey, how are you?

1170
01:45:19,120 --> 01:45:21,719
Mr Ateş, many documents have
piled up waiting for your signature.

1171
01:45:21,720 --> 01:45:23,800
Would you like me to
send them to the mansion?

1172
01:45:25,160 --> 01:45:26,160
Is that so?

1173
01:45:26,640 --> 01:45:29,000
Okay then, I'll give them to Mr Cemal.

1174
01:45:30,320 --> 01:45:32,080
Talk to you later.

1175
01:45:35,040 --> 01:45:38,720
Mr Ateş never used to
neglect his work this much.

1176
01:45:39,320 --> 01:45:41,040
Clearly, they're going through tough times.

1177
01:45:41,440 --> 01:45:42,680
Though his voice sounded fine.

1178
01:45:43,080 --> 01:45:44,080
Anyway.

1179
01:45:44,400 --> 01:45:45,400
Yes.

1180
01:45:45,800 --> 01:45:48,160
Mercan's health isn't very good.

1181
01:45:49,080 --> 01:45:50,080
Okay, see you.

1182
01:45:52,560 --> 01:45:54,600
Burak is so lucky!

1183
01:45:54,880 --> 01:45:57,000
Roaming around Italy.

1184
01:45:57,160 --> 01:45:59,240
Ah, I should be there right now.

1185
01:45:59,720 --> 01:46:01,640
Yaşar Bey, first of all...

1186
01:46:02,200 --> 01:46:04,120
You need to realize this.

1187
01:46:04,520 --> 01:46:06,040
Burak isn't just roaming around there.

1188
01:46:06,160 --> 01:46:08,080
I don't think he's just
having a holiday either.

1189
01:46:08,200 --> 01:46:10,760
He's there for a very important project.

1190
01:46:12,000 --> 01:46:13,000
Let the kid travel/enjoy.

1191
01:46:13,960 --> 01:46:15,120
He's worked hard, he's tired.

1192
01:46:17,240 --> 01:46:19,960
It's really nice that
you two remained friends.

1193
01:46:20,920 --> 01:46:22,840
There's no reason to be enemies.

1194
01:46:23,320 --> 01:46:24,880
We couldn't get along, and that was it.

1195
01:46:25,640 --> 01:46:26,960
Burak is a good kid.

1196
01:46:27,760 --> 01:46:28,760
Yes.

1197
01:46:29,560 --> 01:46:30,840
And rich now.

1198
01:46:37,440 --> 01:46:38,640
Hello Mr Cemal.

1199
01:46:38,880 --> 01:46:42,680
There are some documents that Mr Ateş needs
to sign. He asked me to give them to you.

1200
01:46:43,160 --> 01:46:45,240
Okay. Prepare them, I'll take them.

1201
01:46:45,560 --> 01:46:46,720
I'll prepare them right away.

1202
01:46:47,240 --> 01:46:48,240
Thanks.

1203
01:46:49,040 --> 01:46:50,040
How are you?

1204
01:46:50,880 --> 01:46:53,000
I'm fine, thank you.

1205
01:47:00,240 --> 01:47:01,280
Shall we talk a bit?

1206
01:47:02,800 --> 01:47:03,800
Of course.

1207
01:47:11,680 --> 01:47:14,400
They'll go and talk secretly now.
We won't be able to hear anything.

1208
01:47:15,120 --> 01:47:18,000
You need to stop this
gossiping immediately.

1209
01:47:18,560 --> 01:47:21,160
Please just get back
to your place, honestly!

1210
01:47:22,280 --> 01:47:25,520
I say the same things
to you every day, Yaşar.

1211
01:47:26,480 --> 01:47:28,720
Ms Zahide, you need to
know how to enjoy life.

1212
01:47:29,840 --> 01:47:32,440
Now how are we supposed to learn
what's happening in the company?

1213
01:47:32,720 --> 01:47:34,680
Someone has to do this at the company.

1214
01:47:35,280 --> 01:47:36,280
And that someone is me.

1215
01:47:36,400 --> 01:47:37,400
But I can't hear them.

1216
01:47:55,080 --> 01:47:56,480
I'm still thinking about Mercan.

1217
01:47:57,800 --> 01:47:58,800
How is she?

1218
01:48:00,920 --> 01:48:03,160
I mean... She was well today.

1219
01:48:03,880 --> 01:48:05,920
She went out with Ateş.
She seemed in good spirits.

1220
01:48:07,320 --> 01:48:08,320
I know Mercan.

1221
01:48:09,440 --> 01:48:11,280
What she learned hit her very hard.

1222
01:48:12,560 --> 01:48:14,400
She will feel guilty
for the rest of her life.

1223
01:48:15,440 --> 01:48:20,200
This is a very heavy burden for
anyone with a heart, a conscience.

1224
01:48:20,720 --> 01:48:22,520
It's very normal for Mercan to be affected.

1225
01:48:24,480 --> 01:48:27,120
How nice that none of you blame Mercan…

1226
01:48:28,360 --> 01:48:30,920
Do Ms Müzeyyen and Aslı know this?

1227
01:48:32,040 --> 01:48:34,480
I mean, that you don't blame Mercan.

1228
01:48:35,280 --> 01:48:37,440
Demet, what are you trying to imply?

1229
01:48:38,480 --> 01:48:41,079
If I don't have control
over my own feelings,

1230
01:48:41,080 --> 01:48:42,720
then how am I any different from a slave?

1231
01:48:45,240 --> 01:48:48,000
I'm so sorry, I'm rambling.

1232
01:48:49,480 --> 01:48:52,720
But admit it, your family is a
bit difficult to get along with.

1233
01:48:53,520 --> 01:48:56,160
Don't they make you want to run away?

1234
01:48:57,320 --> 01:48:59,400
Doesn't Nezir make you want to run away?

1235
01:49:00,440 --> 01:49:01,960
He's not exactly a good person either.

1236
01:49:04,360 --> 01:49:05,360
Yes, I admit.

1237
01:49:06,280 --> 01:49:07,720
Sometimes he's truly unbearable.

1238
01:49:09,520 --> 01:49:10,720
But he's a good brother.

1239
01:49:11,840 --> 01:49:13,560
Try looking at it from his perspective too.

1240
01:49:14,160 --> 01:49:16,480
If it weren't for you all,
they would have gotten married.

1241
01:49:17,320 --> 01:49:19,040
He's not going through an easy time either.

1242
01:49:19,360 --> 01:49:21,720
Demet… we're talking about unrequited love.

1243
01:49:22,960 --> 01:49:26,480
These things can't be forced.
They shouldn't be, I mean.

1244
01:49:29,440 --> 01:49:30,440
Admit it.

1245
01:49:30,760 --> 01:49:32,840
At first, Ateş was no different from Nezir.

1246
01:49:33,840 --> 01:49:35,960
I haven't forgotten that
he was forced into marriage.

1247
01:49:37,400 --> 01:49:38,800
They are two very different things.

1248
01:49:39,360 --> 01:49:42,536
From the very first moment, both Mercan's
and Ateş's hearts beat for each other.

1249
01:49:42,560 --> 01:49:45,120
It just took them time to realize
it, that's a different matter.

1250
01:49:46,760 --> 01:49:49,520
I guess sometimes that's how it is.

1251
01:49:57,640 --> 01:50:01,000
Yes. Realizing takes time.

1252
01:50:08,120 --> 01:50:09,480
I have to go.

1253
01:50:09,960 --> 01:50:10,960
See you.

1254
01:51:02,120 --> 01:51:03,120
What happened?

1255
01:51:06,320 --> 01:51:07,760
I don't want to go into the mansion.

1256
01:51:12,000 --> 01:51:13,000
Come with me.

1257
01:51:16,560 --> 01:51:17,560
Aslı!

1258
01:51:18,520 --> 01:51:19,520
Aslı!

1259
01:51:20,680 --> 01:51:22,480
Don't you dare go after
them and bother them.

1260
01:51:25,080 --> 01:51:26,720
My intention is to bother them!

1261
01:51:26,760 --> 01:51:27,960
What do you want?!

1262
01:51:28,120 --> 01:51:29,320
Let go of them already.

1263
01:51:30,080 --> 01:51:32,040
I won't stop until Ateş
separates from Mercan!

1264
01:51:33,080 --> 01:51:35,480
Seeing them together is worse than death!

1265
01:51:35,560 --> 01:51:37,200
Aslı, for God's sake, stop now!

1266
01:51:37,320 --> 01:51:38,840
What kind of dream are you living in!

1267
01:51:39,440 --> 01:51:41,320
Despite everything,
Ateş hasn't given her up.

1268
01:51:41,680 --> 01:51:43,520
Ateş is madly in love with her.

1269
01:51:45,360 --> 01:51:47,120
In the end, you'll be
the one who gets hurt.

1270
01:51:47,600 --> 01:51:48,600
You will lose.

1271
01:51:49,120 --> 01:51:50,240
I'm already hurt!

1272
01:51:51,320 --> 01:51:53,040
I hate seeing that girl happy.

1273
01:51:53,280 --> 01:51:56,480
Am I supposed to just stand by while
that girl is happy while I'm in this state?

1274
01:51:57,240 --> 01:51:58,840
I will never give them peace.

1275
01:52:00,000 --> 01:52:01,000
You won't succeed.

1276
01:52:03,320 --> 01:52:04,320
Is that so?

1277
01:52:06,160 --> 01:52:07,160
Fine.

1278
01:52:07,240 --> 01:52:09,520
Then I'll tell Ateş
that I'm in love with him.

1279
01:52:11,760 --> 01:52:15,400
If you didn't know that it
would push him away you would.

1280
01:52:23,360 --> 01:52:25,320
I'm going to lose my mind, Cemal.

1281
01:52:26,320 --> 01:52:28,800
I can't stand seeing them together.

1282
01:52:31,400 --> 01:52:32,560
Why doesn't he see me?

1283
01:52:34,160 --> 01:52:35,680
Doesn't he see my love for him?

1284
01:52:38,240 --> 01:52:39,440
Stop torturing yourself.

1285
01:52:57,920 --> 01:52:58,920
Aslı!

1286
01:53:00,120 --> 01:53:01,680
I'm fine, okay, nothing's wrong.

1287
01:53:04,040 --> 01:53:05,320
Get inside quickly!

1288
01:53:13,320 --> 01:53:15,040
I've told you before.

1289
01:53:15,920 --> 01:53:17,520
Birds of a feather flock together.

1290
01:53:19,160 --> 01:53:20,320
Don't cross the line, Cemal.

1291
01:54:00,200 --> 01:54:01,440
Do you want to go on the slide?

1292
01:54:01,960 --> 01:54:02,960
Okay.

1293
01:54:03,320 --> 01:54:04,760
Okay, but don't be gentle.

1294
01:54:05,160 --> 01:54:06,880
I want to swing as fast as possible.

1295
01:54:08,360 --> 01:54:09,360
As if I don't know.

1296
01:54:10,440 --> 01:54:13,800
When we were kids, you always used to shout
"faster" when I pushed you on the swing.

1297
01:54:19,160 --> 01:54:20,160
Come on, get on.

1298
01:54:24,080 --> 01:54:25,320
Want to go on together?

1299
01:54:28,040 --> 01:54:29,040
We might fall.

1300
01:54:29,280 --> 01:54:30,400
Are you scared?

1301
01:54:32,320 --> 01:54:33,320
Of the swing?

1302
01:54:36,720 --> 01:54:37,720
No.

1303
01:54:40,160 --> 01:54:41,160
I meant for you.

1304
01:54:44,560 --> 01:54:45,680
You'll protect me.

1305
01:54:53,680 --> 01:54:56,400
Come on, like in that
novel... Just the two of us.

1306
01:55:01,520 --> 01:55:02,520
Okay.

1307
01:55:52,240 --> 01:55:53,240
I love you.

1308
01:55:55,680 --> 01:55:56,680
I love you.

1309
01:56:48,560 --> 01:56:49,640
I brought the lemons.

1310
01:56:51,040 --> 01:56:54,360
For years, pickles in this
house have been made with vinegar.

1311
01:56:54,880 --> 01:56:56,280
And they always turn out delicious.

1312
01:56:56,360 --> 01:56:58,800
Nonsense, the best
pickles are made with lemon.

1313
01:56:59,240 --> 01:57:00,440
No, they're made with vinegar!

1314
01:57:00,760 --> 01:57:01,760
With lemon!
With vinegar!

1315
01:57:02,640 --> 01:57:03,440
With lemon!

1316
01:57:03,441 --> 01:57:04,840
-Vinegar! -Lemon!

1317
01:57:04,920 --> 01:57:06,000
It's made with vinegar!

1318
01:57:06,920 --> 01:57:10,080
Are we really going to have a
childish fight over pickles now!

1319
01:57:10,880 --> 01:57:13,760
This house has rules, you
can't just come and change them.

1320
01:57:14,400 --> 01:57:16,320
The rules of this house
have changed now, Çiçek.

1321
01:57:16,680 --> 01:57:18,080
Ms Nermin isn't the only boss.

1322
01:57:18,480 --> 01:57:20,400
Ms Nermin likes pickles with lemon.

1323
01:57:21,000 --> 01:57:22,560
Ms Nermin likes them with vinegar.

1324
01:57:22,680 --> 01:57:25,600
-Lemon! -Vinegar!

1325
01:57:27,000 --> 01:57:28,000
Lemon!

1326
01:57:28,080 --> 01:57:29,760
Stop arguing!

1327
01:57:30,080 --> 01:57:34,216
Instead of trying to out-talk each other, if you just
did your work, it would have been finished long ago!

1328
01:57:34,240 --> 01:57:35,240
Mom...

1329
01:57:35,640 --> 01:57:37,880
But she wants to make them with lemon, Mom.

1330
01:57:39,880 --> 01:57:43,120
Make half with lemon, half with vinegar!

1331
01:57:47,320 --> 01:57:49,080
Don't you have anything
else to worry about?

1332
01:57:49,480 --> 01:57:50,480
See?

1333
01:57:51,040 --> 01:57:53,456
My mother-in-law is speaking, so
it must be right. I'm not ignorant.

1334
01:57:53,480 --> 01:57:54,800
I know how to make pickles.

1335
01:57:59,880 --> 01:58:01,920
Fine, here, make them all with vinegar.

1336
01:58:02,160 --> 01:58:03,160
I'm not getting involved.

1337
01:58:04,680 --> 01:58:06,600
I'll make some with my mom later.

1338
01:58:07,160 --> 01:58:08,160
My dear mother.

1339
01:58:17,000 --> 01:58:19,360
Çiçek, I never expected this from you.

1340
01:58:19,560 --> 01:58:21,920
You've turned into a full-fledged
oppressive sister-in-law.

1341
01:58:22,320 --> 01:58:24,280
Mom, I don't understand you at all.

1342
01:58:24,720 --> 01:58:27,200
Weren't you the one saying
"I'll make Zehra pay"?

1343
01:58:27,560 --> 01:58:30,000
Now you're defending her against me?

1344
01:58:30,640 --> 01:58:34,680
And last night, you got
up and gave her a bracelet.

1345
01:58:37,080 --> 01:58:41,160
I know how to put Zehra
in her place when necessary.

1346
01:58:44,520 --> 01:58:46,840
But can you go after her for
every little thing like this?

1347
01:58:46,880 --> 01:58:48,640
Besides, your brother
loves Zehra very much.

1348
01:58:48,800 --> 01:58:51,560
The boy gets upset when
we make faces at her.

1349
01:58:59,760 --> 01:59:04,239
I'll make half with lemon later with Zehra.

1350
01:59:04,240 --> 01:59:05,600
You make yours with vinegar.

1351
01:59:05,760 --> 01:59:07,640
No, I'm making all of them with vinegar.

1352
01:59:08,000 --> 01:59:08,560
Çiçek!

1353
01:59:08,800 --> 01:59:12,080
Come on, mind your own business. There's
tons of work, is pickle our only problem?

1354
01:59:13,840 --> 01:59:15,000
I'm making them with vinegar.

1355
01:59:19,000 --> 01:59:20,960
Don't make me angry, Çiçek!

1356
01:59:40,400 --> 01:59:42,160
Hello Malik!

1357
01:59:42,440 --> 01:59:44,480
Hello Cemal Bey.

1358
01:59:45,960 --> 01:59:49,960
We talked already, but
it's finally settled now.

1359
01:59:50,400 --> 01:59:51,600
You can be completely at ease.

1360
01:59:51,920 --> 01:59:53,840
Oh! Thank goodness!

1361
01:59:54,760 --> 01:59:57,360
I don't know what to say, how to thank you.

1362
01:59:57,840 --> 01:59:59,720
You tried so hard. You
called and asked around.

1363
01:59:59,840 --> 02:00:00,880
You put in effort for me.

1364
02:00:01,120 --> 02:00:02,480
Don't mention it, Malik.

1365
02:00:03,160 --> 02:00:07,400
I almost had to leave Çiçek.

1366
02:00:08,320 --> 02:00:13,640
As long as you're around here,
whatever you need, come to us, Malik.

1367
02:00:13,680 --> 02:00:15,520
We'll do whatever we can.

1368
02:00:15,880 --> 02:00:18,200
Thank you very much, Mr Cemal.

1369
02:00:19,920 --> 02:00:21,800
Mr Cemal, I want to ask you something.

1370
02:00:23,320 --> 02:00:25,280
You had told me that someone reported me.

1371
02:00:27,200 --> 02:00:28,200
Yes.

1372
02:00:28,400 --> 02:00:32,640
I don't know anyone in Istanbul
besides the people in the mansion.

1373
02:00:34,560 --> 02:00:36,400
And the people here wouldn't report me.

1374
02:00:37,600 --> 02:00:39,416
Why are you bothering
with such things, Malik?

1375
02:00:39,440 --> 02:00:40,880
Never mind, it's over and done with.

1376
02:00:40,920 --> 02:00:42,040
We sorted it out in the end.

1377
02:00:42,640 --> 02:00:43,200
It's fine now.

1378
02:00:43,600 --> 02:00:45,120
That's true, of course, but...

1379
02:00:45,960 --> 02:00:48,640
If you know, please tell me who it was.

1380
02:01:31,640 --> 02:01:32,840
I don't want to see him.

1381
02:01:38,680 --> 02:01:40,000
I don't want to see him, but...

1382
02:01:40,560 --> 02:01:42,680
My heart doesn't consent
to him staying there either.

1383
02:01:46,880 --> 02:01:48,440
Will you think about this matter again?

1384
02:02:02,840 --> 02:02:03,840
Oh, patience…

1385
02:02:04,480 --> 02:02:07,680
I'm tired of throwing this guy out, but
he never gets tired of being thrown out.

1386
02:02:13,520 --> 02:02:15,616
I'm tired of beating him, but
he's not tired of being beaten.

1387
02:02:15,640 --> 02:02:16,640
Ateş.

1388
02:02:17,120 --> 02:02:19,280
Please, let's not have any tension. Please.

1389
02:02:21,160 --> 02:02:22,160
Mercan.

1390
02:02:30,760 --> 02:02:32,080
Ateş, would you give us a moment?

1391
02:02:42,320 --> 02:02:43,600
I wondered how you were, Mercan.

1392
02:02:46,000 --> 02:02:47,000
Nezir.

1393
02:02:47,400 --> 02:02:49,080
I told you I would think about it, but...

1394
02:02:50,000 --> 02:02:51,640
Actually, there's nothing to think about.

1395
02:02:53,360 --> 02:02:55,640
I know you're worried
about me, that you care.

1396
02:02:56,080 --> 02:02:57,360
You're very thoughtful.

1397
02:02:58,440 --> 02:03:00,040
But you need to put an end to this now.

1398
02:03:05,240 --> 02:03:06,560
Please don't come anymore.

1399
02:03:08,600 --> 02:03:09,600
I can't.

1400
02:03:11,240 --> 02:03:12,240
I can't, Mercan.

1401
02:03:13,160 --> 02:03:14,880
What you're going through upsets me.

1402
02:03:17,240 --> 02:03:18,240
Please, Nezir.

1403
02:03:18,800 --> 02:03:20,560
I'm tired of talking about the same things.

1404
02:03:22,080 --> 02:03:24,280
You're ruining your own life too.

1405
02:03:29,160 --> 02:03:30,800
You have to get me out of your mind now.

1406
02:03:32,080 --> 02:03:34,720
Forget me and go your own way.

1407
02:03:36,560 --> 02:03:37,560
No.

1408
02:03:38,440 --> 02:03:40,320
You know very well I can't do that.

1409
02:03:42,640 --> 02:03:43,640
I am patient.

1410
02:03:44,760 --> 02:03:46,880
My offer to you is valid until I die.

1411
02:03:50,240 --> 02:03:51,240
Do you know why?

1412
02:03:52,280 --> 02:03:54,440
Because I know that you and
Ateş cannot have a future.

1413
02:04:02,520 --> 02:04:05,040
The advice you give me, you
should actually give to yourself.

1414
02:04:11,200 --> 02:04:13,481
You should be the one to
forget Ateş and go your own way.

1415
02:04:59,440 --> 02:05:00,440
Come, my daughter.

1416
02:05:10,320 --> 02:05:11,320
How are you?

1417
02:05:12,880 --> 02:05:13,880
I'm better.

1418
02:05:14,680 --> 02:05:16,080
Going to the seaside,

1419
02:05:16,600 --> 02:05:18,000
getting some fresh air did me good…

1420
02:05:20,360 --> 02:05:21,360
How are you?

1421
02:05:24,040 --> 02:05:25,880
How can I be well? After everything.

1422
02:05:31,040 --> 02:05:33,320
Sometimes I seem indifferent, but...

1423
02:05:35,280 --> 02:05:36,400
I'm tired now.

1424
02:05:42,160 --> 02:05:44,320
All I want is to go back to the old days.

1425
02:05:50,520 --> 02:05:51,520
Mercan.

1426
02:05:52,520 --> 02:05:55,480
Can't you convince Ateş
to let your father out?

1427
02:05:57,640 --> 02:05:58,960
He loves you, Mercan.

1428
02:06:00,520 --> 02:06:02,040
He won't listen to anyone but you.

1429
02:06:04,320 --> 02:06:06,640
My father should be grateful
he's not in prison right now.

1430
02:06:11,400 --> 02:06:12,400
You...

1431
02:06:13,400 --> 02:06:15,320
Why didn't you stop my
father regarding Eylül?

1432
02:06:22,520 --> 02:06:24,040
I'm not going to lie to you.

1433
02:06:32,600 --> 02:06:35,080
My only concern was that
my daughter would be saved…

1434
02:06:36,480 --> 02:06:37,480
Because you were dying.

1435
02:06:40,800 --> 02:06:42,200
I didn't know about Eylül.

1436
02:06:44,440 --> 02:06:47,600
But I was also aware that
this was being done illegally.

1437
02:06:50,680 --> 02:06:51,680
Mercan.

1438
02:06:55,480 --> 02:06:57,520
I haven't been a very attentive mother.

1439
02:06:59,640 --> 02:07:02,720
But my children's lives come
before everything else for me.

1440
02:07:04,960 --> 02:07:06,120
Call it whatever you want.

1441
02:07:06,360 --> 02:07:09,120
Selfishness or something else.

1442
02:07:11,320 --> 02:07:13,720
I have no regrets about keeping you alive.

1443
02:07:17,160 --> 02:07:20,040
The price of this kidney I
carry is very heavy, mother.

1444
02:07:22,280 --> 02:07:23,680
If I had a choice...

1445
02:07:25,240 --> 02:07:26,320
I would have chosen to die.

1446
02:07:28,640 --> 02:07:30,120
I won't hear that again.

1447
02:07:31,640 --> 02:07:33,640
There's nothing for
you to feel guilty about!

1448
02:08:27,200 --> 02:08:30,280
Malik, where were you? You
didn't come for lunch either?

1449
02:08:33,880 --> 02:08:35,200
Malik, are you okay?

1450
02:08:37,480 --> 02:08:42,440
I promised you there would be
no more lies between us, Çiçek.

1451
02:08:44,080 --> 02:08:46,120
Malik, what happened? Don't scare me.

1452
02:08:50,000 --> 02:08:51,600
I found out who reported me…

1453
02:09:04,040 --> 02:09:05,200
My father did it.

1454
02:09:07,280 --> 02:09:08,280
Are you sure?

1455
02:09:15,040 --> 02:09:16,360
It's because of me, isn't it?

1456
02:09:18,560 --> 02:09:20,280
They're doing it to make you leave me…

1457
02:09:33,320 --> 02:09:34,400
Please don't be upset.

1458
02:09:35,840 --> 02:09:37,760
Seeing you like this upsets me too.

1459
02:09:43,520 --> 02:09:44,520
I can't help it, Çiçek.

1460
02:09:45,000 --> 02:09:46,080
I'm upset.

1461
02:09:47,160 --> 02:09:48,920
I didn't expect this much from them.

1462
02:09:51,240 --> 02:09:54,680
He did it so you would
return home, to be with them.

1463
02:09:56,840 --> 02:10:00,840
I don't know whether to be angry
with your father or to understand him.

1464
02:10:04,440 --> 02:10:05,440
My home is with you.

1465
02:10:09,520 --> 02:10:11,200
Your family will never accept me, Malik.

1466
02:11:26,920 --> 02:11:27,920
You'll get cold.

1467
02:11:50,160 --> 02:11:51,680
Thank you for today.

1468
02:11:53,360 --> 02:11:54,560
It was a very special day.

1469
02:11:56,760 --> 02:11:58,720
It became one of the days
I will always remember.

1470
02:13:18,160 --> 02:13:20,160
Your hand is cold.
Come on, let's go inside.

1471
02:13:50,880 --> 02:13:51,880
Good night.

1472
02:14:33,040 --> 02:14:34,040
Good night.

1473
02:14:34,160 --> 02:14:35,160
Good night.

1474
02:19:02,840 --> 02:19:03,840
Mercan?

1475
02:20:29,120 --> 02:20:30,280
My eternal love...

1476
02:20:31,800 --> 02:20:34,520
Being apart from you is no
different from death for me.

1477
02:20:35,720 --> 02:20:36,760
But I have to.

1478
02:20:38,200 --> 02:20:39,200
We have to.

1479
02:21:00,200 --> 02:21:02,480
Eylül's shadow will always be between us.

1480
02:21:03,720 --> 02:21:06,920
Every time you look at me, you'll
remember why your sister died.

1481
02:21:08,800 --> 02:21:13,200
I wish our paths had never crossed,
so all this pain wouldn't have happened.

1482
02:21:19,880 --> 02:21:20,880
No.

1483
02:21:21,600 --> 02:21:22,600
No. No. No.

1484
02:21:23,480 --> 02:21:24,480
Don't do this, Mercan.

1485
02:21:26,480 --> 02:21:27,760
Don't do this, Mercan. No.

1486
02:21:39,600 --> 02:21:40,760
But even when we're apart…

1487
02:21:42,000 --> 02:21:43,360
You will always remain within me,

1488
02:21:44,640 --> 02:21:45,840
you will live with me.

1489
02:22:23,840 --> 02:22:25,840
As long as I am well, you will breathe.

1490
02:22:27,120 --> 02:22:28,760
As long as you are well, I will live.

1491
02:22:47,680 --> 02:22:49,120
I'm not saying goodbye to you.

1492
02:22:51,480 --> 02:22:53,680
I'm just learning to love you from afar.

1493
02:22:59,080 --> 02:23:00,080
Mercan?

1494
02:23:08,720 --> 02:23:09,720
My love, my vow...

1495
02:23:10,280 --> 02:23:11,480
My indispensable one...

1496
02:23:12,240 --> 02:23:13,280
My sunshine.

1497
02:23:22,480 --> 02:23:24,280
I am giving you up for your sake.

1498
02:23:25,360 --> 02:23:26,560
I love you so much…

1499
02:23:49,320 --> 02:23:50,720
Don't you leave me too!

1500
02:24:10,840 --> 02:24:11,840
Mercan.

1501
02:24:29,200 --> 02:24:30,200
Mercan!

1502
02:24:57,880 --> 02:24:59,200
You were the only one left.
